title: cantaloupe jam
directions: Place cantaloupe in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Continue boiling for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon, while hot, into hot sterilized jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: bran bread
directions: Sift soda, salt, flour.
Add all ingredients in order with the melted butter or fat last.
Pour in greased 4 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° in oven.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: stuffed buns
directions: Brown meat with other ingredients.
Stuff any kind of buns. Serve.
(Takes 2 packages of hot dog buns.)

title: sole florentine(for 4)
directions: Roll up fish filets and place in pan with clam juice and simmer about 4 minutes or until cooked. Place drained spinach in 8 x 8 casserole and place sole rolls on top. Sprinkle with shrimp. Pour Sauce over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked broccoli
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole, stir all ingredients except broccoli, until well blended.
Add broccoli and toss well.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings. Serve with chicken in wine sauce, paprika mashed potatoes, ice cream parfaits and coffee.

title: broccoli and beef
directions: Stir-fry broccoli and add a small amount of water.
Then add meat, garlic and
onion.
Add
to 1/2 bottle of oyster sauce. Make thickening for
gravy, add and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Put rice on
before
the
rest of the meal and everything will be ready in 1/2 hour.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Mix egg and sugar together until smooth.
Add vinegar and water.
Put over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it starts to boil, turn heat to low and let it boil about 5 to 10 minutes. Add salt and butter to taste.
Cool.
Can be stored in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the berries in a food processor; pour sugar over the cranberries.
Let stand 15 minutes.
In another bowl, mix the unflavored gelatin, orange jello and water; let cool.
Add the gelatin mixture to the cranberries; mix well.
Add the orange and juice, pineapple and pecans.
Pour in a jello mold or container; let thicken.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: *You may use dark or mixed chicken.
You can also boil your own chicken and tear into pieces.

title: chicken wings ginger soy
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soy sauce, sherry, water, garlic and grated ginger.
Add chicken wings and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender, turning once or twice.
Cool in the liquid.
Serve cold.
Makes 16 to 18 appetizers.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Cook broccoli; saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook rice; mix soup and cheese with broccoli.
Add sauteed vegetables; stir in cooked rice.
Season to taste.
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low fat, low cholesterol lite n' creamy garlic dressing
directions: In blender, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over cold milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low speed until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and process at high speed until blended.
Pour into serving bowls and chill until slightly thickened.
Before serving, stir until smooth.
Can be stored covered in refrigerator up to 5 days.
Makes 2 cups dressing.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add Prego.
Simmer.
Cook lasagna as directed.
Spoon layer of sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan, then a layer of noodles, then sauce, then cheese.
Repeat until pan is full. Top layer should be cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is brown and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a greased dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (until brown).

title: chocolate fudge by mama lois
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and salt. Let come to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into Pyrex dish.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut dough into strips; wrap around sausages.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake.
Fold in oranges, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Bake 2 hours at 325°, covered.
Bake an additional hour, uncovered.

title: banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding.
Mix with mixer.
Add Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Mix with mixer.
Slice bananas and add to mixture.
Line oblong pan with vanilla wafers.
Layer pudding mixture and cookies.
Makes a lot!

title: california blend vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables until not quite done.
Melt cheese in soup. Drain vegetables well.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour soup and cheese mixture over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
You can add grated Parmesan cheese to thicken, if needed.

title: sugar free pineapple chess pie
directions: Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: spinach-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
spinach
and broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
Combine sour cream and soup mix; stir into spinach and broccoli.
Season with salt.
Place in casserole. Bake, covered,
in preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and oleo together.
Bake 5 minutes at 350° on cookie sheet.
Cool cake and spread melted caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over cake.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add bay leaf, garlic, onions, salt and bacon.
Simmer slowly until done.
Add tomato puree, dry mustard, oregano, brown sugar, chili powder and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: crab meat stew
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender in Dutch oven over medium flame. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring frequently. Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl; mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Add chips last.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cake is moist and delicious.

title: green chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
In a skillet combine soup and cheese whiz; cook on low until melted.
Add broccoli, rice and chicken to cheese mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Top with cheddar cheese and serve.

title: mother's cinnamon apples
directions: Mix evenly in a large baking pan and cook for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole or 8-inch square pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar to your liking.
Cut biscuits in half, making half circles.
Dip in melted butter, then cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place on top of pie filling.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits are golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: slush
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and freeze.
Thaw to slush. Pour ginger ale over slush.
Serves 20.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Marinate at least 12 hours.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until cheese dissolves.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to hot soup and cool.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: twinkies dessert
directions: Arrange sliced Twinkies in bottom of a clear, long dish. Spread crushed pineapple on top of these. Put sliced bananas on top of this.
(Bananas can be dipped in lemon juice to prevent them from turning dark.)

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange juice and dissolve. Drain oranges.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to set overnight.

title: dorothy's apple cake
directions: Mix chopped apples and sugar.
Let stand till sugar dissolves. Add beaten egg and stir.
Sift flour, cinnamon, and baking soda and add to apple mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix soup and peppers together. Melt Velvetta in a double boiler. Add soup mixture. Heat thoroughly. Serve in a chafing dish. Serve with Doritos or Tostito chips.

title: pasta in one pot
directions: In a large pot, bring everything to a boil.
Cover and simmer 16 to 18 minutes.
Stir twice.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cocoa and hot liquid.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream lard and sugar; add eggs, beating 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and then flour mixture, alternating with cocoa mix.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350°.

title: race-day mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread in bottom of 9x13 dish.
Layer next six ingredients in order they are listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: special chicken
directions: Put chicken, skin side down, in baking dish.
Pour butter over it.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes more. Stir soup and add to chicken with seasonings.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, into one bowl.
Beat with mixer or by hand for 4 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The pie will settle in middle as it cools.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased jellyroll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch, pinching edges together.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; beat until well blended.
Spread mixture over crust. Sprinkle with cheese and vegetables.
Chill 2 hours; cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch bites.
Yield: 8 dozen.

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: Cut up fruit.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and jello together with fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes and put in pie shell.
Put a couple of tablespoons of butter on top of fruit, then the top
crust. Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Follow directions for devil's food cake mix and bake in 2 round layer pans. Cut the layers each in half so you have four layers.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion in saucepan; add celery soup and milk.
Heat.
Add potatoes and sausage, cut in pieces.
Place in medium casserole; top with 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Add 4 to 5 whole sausages.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly. Kids love it and it's easy and inexpensive!

title: flounder fillets in foil(low calorie)
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion in oleo; add all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together; put into greased pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with catsup.
Place back in oven; cook another 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice and place 1 slice of pineapple between slices.
Place maraschino cherries on each slice of meat loaf.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. With fork stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Knead about 10 times to form a ball. Don't overknead.
Roll out to 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With knife, cut dough into 12 portions. Don't separate; leave biscuits in a square.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Mix these ingredients together and knead until smooth.
Firm in refrigerator prior to dipping.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and turn into oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Freeze.
Take out about 15 minutes before serving. Cut into squares.

title: apricot casserole
directions: In long flat dish, spread apricots evenly over bottom.
Top with oleo pats.
Crush, not crumble, crackers over top of butter pats.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm as accompaniment for pork or chicken dishes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix together and drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 275° until light brown. Makes about 200 cookies.

title: low sugar diabetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water until all water is absorbed.
Add applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn dough into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Yields 20 servings (about 150 calories per serving).

title: high fiber oatmeal bread
directions: Follow the directions for your bread machine.
For a variation, add 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon or 1/2 cup raisins to recipe.

title: bobbie's french onion soup
directions: Slice onions very thin; brown in 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon flour and a pinch of sugar.
Add beef broth, water, wine, bouillon cube, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Add croutons; sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: cheese strata(breakfast casserole)
directions: Trim crusts and lightly butter bread.
Brown sausage.
Place 6 slices of bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased (spray with Pam) baking dish, buttered side up.
Spread 1/2 crumbled, drained sausage or bacon and cheese over bread.
Place 6 slices of bread on top, followed by rest of sausage and cheese.
Lightly beat together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Press down with spatula until milk comes through.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Can add mushrooms.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring vinegar, oil, sugar and soup to a boil.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate.
Keeps four weeks or more.
Best after sets one week.

title: pork chops with gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in large skillet with 1 tablespoon oil. After pork chops are browned, place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix 1/4 cup milk and 1/2 cup water together.
Put this in the skillet that you just fried pork chops in and warm through.
Add the cream of mushroom soup; mix well and pour over the pork chops. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes until smooth.
Add cubed cream cheese.
Whip. Add garlic salt and 1 cup sour cream.
Place in a 2-quart casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or may be put in the deep freeze and warmed in microwave.

title: gumbo
directions: Cut meat
into	small cubes, roll in flour and brown in margarine
in
uncovered
14-inch Dutch oven.
Add salt, water and onion.
Cover
and	cook
for
1 hour.
Add tomatoes, bell pepper, okra, thyme, tarragon and bay leaf.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours. Replenish coals as needed.

title: frosty with fruit
directions: Combine blueberries, peaches and milk in a blender. Cover and process on high. Add yogurt, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg; blend well. Serve in chilled glasses

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little bits of love.
Bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.

title: soy marinade
directions: In large shallow dish or plastic bag, combine ingredients; add beef, chicken or pork.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade; heat thoroughly.
Grill or broil meat as desired, basting frequently with marinade.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
Approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Debone and cut into bite size pieces. Wilt tortillas in chicken stock.
Mix soups and tomatoes in bowl. Layer in 9 x 12 baking dish in this order:
tortillas, chicken, pepper, onion, cheese, chili powder, and garlic powder.
Spread soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey and sausage gumbo
directions: Use a turkey carcass with a little meat left on it.
A smoked turkey is best.
Cover carcass with water and boil until meat leaves bones (about 1 hour).
Reserve broth and remove meat from carcass; discard bones.
Combine salad oil and flour in a large iron pot;.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a medium brown roux is formed.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; cook about 5 minutes or until tender, stirring constantly.
Add sausage, turkey and 2 to 3 quarts broth (add water to make 2 quarts if necessary).
Simmer 1 hour.
Season gumbo to taste with salt and peppers.
Stir in parsley and green onion.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Thicken with file, if desired. Serves 8 to 10.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar while continuing to beat egg whites.
Add vanilla and salt.
Carefully fold in chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cookies in oven and turn oven "off."
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door until morning!
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
Final product will be white and resemble divinity but will be crunchy.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together; shape into firm roll.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Place in a cooking bag that has around 1 tablespoon flour in bottom.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove wrap and cool.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Serve with your favorite crackers and cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 4 skinned chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix celery and mushroom soups with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over chicken.
Top with bamboo shoots, mushroom pieces, drained and sliced chestnut pieces, drained.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with vegetables or rice and rolls.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 pans. Beat eggs, oil, apples, sugar and vanilla on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed, scraping occasionally, until moistened, about 15 seconds. Beat on medium speed 45 seconds. Stir in nuts and raisins. Spread in pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool remainder on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: taco pie
directions: om of pie shell and bake 10 minutes.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Add taco mix according to directions on package.
In small mixing bowl, combine refried beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Mix well.
Layer refried bean mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Top with half seasoned meat, 1 cup cheese and chips. Repeat except leave off chips.
Bake.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and remainder of sauce and cheese.

title: tomato pan gravy
directions: Pan saute onion
and fresh tomatoes until soft.
Add pan drippings and flour.
Stir
in
water, stirring as gravy thickens. Serve over rice, goes well with golden brown pork chops!

title: mandarin roast
directions: Brown beef roast and onion in hot oil.
Pour oranges on top. Mix ketchup and sauce and put over roast.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each one in 4 pieces. Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture and place in Bundt pan. Continue until all cans are done. With remaining sugar and cinnamon, melt butter in microwave. Stir and if it is too buttery, add sugar until thicker. Pour over biscuits in pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven. Bake until golden brown. Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes and turn out on plate.

title: lamb stew
directions: Coat meat with flour and brown.
Add 3 cups water, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: barbecue steak
directions: Blend together the first 8 ingredients.
Cut steak into small strips.
Flour until well coated.
Heat shortening in skillet and brown well.
Add onion and let brown around meat.
Pour the blended ingredients over meat.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and form into ball. Roll in pecans.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer as listed, using a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare 24 hours ahead.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Note:
Biscuits can be substituted for sliced bread.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups sugar, the stick of oleo and the 2 eggs into bowl; cream well. Add the fruit cocktail with juice, then the flour, soda and vanilla. Pour into large, greased floured pan. Sprinkle with the chopped pecans and brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When done, poke holes in cake and cover with topping.

title: thai chicken salad
directions: Poach chicken in salted water until opaque.
Drain and shred into pieces.
Toss dressing with chicken.
Add sprouts and peppers; serve over mixed greens.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut evenly over bottom of pan. Pour prepared cake mix over this.
Melt margarine in large bowl and stir in sour cream and powdered sugar.
Pour this over cake. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back in center.

title: spaghetti-hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and green peppers; drain.
Add both soups and water.
Add garlic powder and lightly salt and pepper.
Place drained spaghetti in lightly greased pan.
Add other ingredients. Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean soup
directions: In large kettle, cook beans and potatoes.
While they are cooking, fry bacon until almost crisp.
Take bacon out and add it to beans and potatoes.
Keep drippings in pan.
Add salt, pepper and parsley flakes to taste.
Heat fat in pan and add flour. Brown as for gravy.
When as brown as desired, add water; stir until it thickens.
Add to soup; let simmer.
Add vinegar to soup; simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Longer won't matter.
Serve hot.

title: nail soup
directions: Brown onions. Add to large soup pot full of water.
Add chopped vegetables, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: micro italian potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in large pieces and coat with oil. Place on a 9 or 10-inch baking pan. Cover with sliced onion and tomatoes.
Add seasonings. Cover with wax paper or plastic.
Microwave on High for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin meringue pie
directions: Combine pumpkin with sugar, spices and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in egg yolks.
Gradually blend in evaporated milk.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes or until knife comes clean.
Make meringue from the egg whites.
Spoon meringue over pie filling, spreading evenly to edge of crust to seal all around.
Bake in a 425° oven for 5 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: make ahead biscuits
directions: Mix flour and oil.
Mix dry yeast with water.
Blend in flour and yeast.
Add other ingredients.
Chill in bowl.
Roll a little thicker than usual.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Mixture will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: spicy tomato
directions: Mix soup per instructions.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put onion in blender.
Blend until it is juice.
Then add oil, vinegar and dry ingredients.
Blend until it's thick and creamy.

title: todd's bacon and cheese morning muffins
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings.
If necessary, add oil to drippings to measure 1/3 cup.
In a small bowl, combine dripping mixture, egg and milk; set aside.
Crumble bacon; set aside.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix all together; beat until fluffy.
Bake in 3 layer pans or in Bundt pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar for 2 minutes.
Add Ritz crackers and boil 2 more minutes longer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter or oleo. Adjust top crust and bake until brown.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Melt cheese and soup.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine ingredients for sauce.
Line baking dish with broccoli then put in chicken.
Pour sauce over whole thing.
Put croutons on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: veal stew
directions: Put 2 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons of oil in a stockpot and turn on to medium-high heat.
Coat veal cubes with flour.
When butter foam subsides, add cubes.
Cook cubes until all sides are browned.
Transfer cubes to plate using slotted spoon. Turn heat to medium.
Add onion.
Cook until translucent and add garlic.
When softened, add 1 cup of wine.
Let boil a few seconds.
Return meat to pan.
Add tomato sauce, rosemary, sage, parsley, salt and pepper.
Adjust heat to a gentle simmer and cover pan.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes or more.
Turn from time to time until meat is tender.
While meat is cooking, prepared mushrooms.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put one pie shell on bottom. Put ingredients in pie shell, then the other one on top.
Mash the sides together. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sand paint
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Stir.
Pour into pastry bags.
Draw or trace any picture.
This works best on freezer paper.
Another kids favorite!

title: dirt
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix French vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Add creamed mixture and mix. Layer in pan with crushed Oreo cookies.

title: jennifer's delicious cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, using package directions.
Let cake cool.
Pierce cooled cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Drizzle condensed milk and sauce over cake. Let stand for 1 hour.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: salsa
directions: Blend tomatoes and chopped onion in a blender.
Pour into bowl.
Add as much of the other ingredients as you like (a little at a time).

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Bake until eggs set.
Lay slices of bread in baking dish. Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients, except syrup, which is used on top of baked pudding.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool before slicing.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush crackers.
Mix crackers with Parmesan cheese and garlic.
Melt margarine, then dip chicken in margarine and roll in cracker crumb mixture.
Place chicken in pan that has been sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Let chicken cook for 1 hour.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Work together until soft enough to roll.
Roll on board about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Prick with fork.
Bake in hot oven for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: miniature brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 72 mini-muffin tins with fluted-foil baking cups or arrange baking cups on cookie sheet. Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.

title: wild rice elegance(i use this for pork or chicken)
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Set aside. Saute onion, mushrooms and green pepper in margarine until tender. Stir in rice, apple and pecans.
Heat until thoroughly heated.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Drop teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet covered with foil.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients. Stir into egg mixture. Shape into balls.
Roll in additional granulated sugar, then make imprint with fork that has been dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy sausage stew
directions: Place vegetables and sausage in ovenproof pot.
Mix oil and spices.
Pour onto vegetable mix and toss to coat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add chip dip to milk and mix until smooth.
Add to pot and stir.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mix water and cornstarch and add to pot.
Put on stove top and boil until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces of almond bark in a large saucepan or microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut. Melt remaining 2 ounces almond bark; drizzle over coconut.
Chill until firm.
Set out at room temperature for serving.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by ice cream scoop.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lena's creamy onion-and-potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 1 minute or until onion is tender.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and next 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in nondairy creamer and heat thoroughly.
Garnish, if desired. Yields 7 cups.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Leave butter out to soften at room temperature.
Mix with milk and work in sifted powdered sugar, coconut and pecans.
This mixture will be stiff and will have to be worked with hands. Place mixture in refrigerator for 10 minutes, then shape into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate together in double boiler. When dissolved and stirred, dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: beer peanuts
directions: Heat all over medium heat.
As it begins to boil, stir frequently to keep nuts covered.
Put nuts on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Turn nuts over; continue to bake 20 minutes longer or until nuts are roasted.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half.
Layer on bottom of pan.
Make instant pudding with 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Blend Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk into pudding.
Pour mixture over Twinkies.
Chill. Pour strawberries on top before serving.
I put the strawberries on top, then chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onion and margarine until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add cheese and saltines.
Mix eggs and milk; add to squash.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cover-up
directions: Arrange broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread on sauce made of rest of ingredients.
Heat at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Place flank steak in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour marinade over steak, turning to glaze all sides.
Prick with fork on both sides.
Cover and chill for 24 to 48 hours, turning and pricking several times.
Remove steak from marinade; broil at 500° for 6 minutes on each side or cook over a charcoal grill until desired doneness.

title: applesauce diet cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all the water is cooked out.
Cool slightly.
Mix applesauce, eggs and Sweet 'N Low.
Add cinnamon and oil; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour 1 cup at a time until all is mixed in well.
Add raisins last, mixing well and pour into a large tube pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 1 hour.

title: pig-eating good cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool cake.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixer bowl at high speed until very stiff; set aside.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a mixing bowl. Add sour cream and mix well. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers or bread chunks. Makes 12 servings.

title: date nut bread
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend all together.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of lime jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add 2 cups cold water and pour into dish and chill.

title: dressing casserole
directions: Make up the dressing.
Put a good layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the soup and milk.
On top of dressing, place remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday cider
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and discard. Stir in rum extract.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add slightly beaten eggs and vinegar. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° about 30 minutes or until brown and set.

title: grammie's dig deep salad
directions: Layer lettuce, red onions, green peppers, celery, water chestnuts and green peas in a serving bowl in order given.
Spread mayonnaise over the top layer.
Sprinkle with cheese; do not stir. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients to this mixture.
Add carrots, packed firmly.
These may be grated or put through food grinder, using finest blade.
Add vanilla and nut meats.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Like all quick breads, this improves with aging for a day or so.

title: marcia's twice baked potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as box describes in a glass bowl in microwave. May layer or mix sour cream in potatoes by choice.

title: old-fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix well egg, sugar and flour.
Melt margarine in Pyrex dish and pur over sugar and eggs.
Stir well.
Add buttermilk.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pans or use paper muffin cups. Finely grate orange peel.
Finely chop pecans.
Beat butter and sugar together until pale and creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in soda and peel.
Fold in half of the flour and half of the milk.
Repeat.
Fold in pecans.
Scoop into cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven.
Brush with orange juice and sprinkle with sugar.

title: french meat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and cook about 2 hours until water evaporates.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
When knife comes out clean, casserole is done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and add chicken.
Put in 9 X 13 baking dish and top with grated Cheddar cheese or Mozzarella.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tayla's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Combine all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Butter the sides of baking dish.
Pour in mixture and top with ritz crackers.
Then pat with butter.
Bake for 45-50 minutes at 350 degrees or until brown.
May be reheated and will remain soft.

title: herb sticks
directions: Mix herbs, garlic salt and margarine. Split buns in half then lengthwise. Spread each piece with herb mixture. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 250 for 1 hour. Leaven in oven 1 1/2 hours with oven off.

title: hot 'n  hearty potato salad
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook onions in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in next 5 ingredients, then add potatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated through. Garnish with parsley and bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil sugar, water and spices for 15 minutes.
Add juices and tea.
Heat or serve cold.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Use powdered sugar to dip hands into as you roll balls.
Melt chocolate squares and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls into mixture, one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Drop onto wax paper (moist inside, hard outside). Stays fresh for weeks.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain off any grease and add seasoning.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, tomato sauce, chili sauce, stewed tomatoes and ketchup. Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: my pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and sugar together, then mix last 3 ingredients together in a cup.
Mix into your flour mixture and divide into separate crusts.
Put in refrigerator until ready to roll out.
Can also freeze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Add flour.
Stir in egg yolk with milk.
Add margarine.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Add meringue made with egg whites and 5 tablespoons sugar.

title: walnut oatmeal shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
Fit work bowl with metal blade.
Add walnuts and chop with 5 or 6 on/off pulses or until very finely chopped.
Add oats and blend together with nuts, about 3 seconds.
Remove from work bowl and reserve.
Add flour, salt and baking soda to work bowl, still fitted with metal blade.
Process just until mixed, about 3 seconds.
Remove and reserve.
Cut butter into 1-inch cubes and add to work bowl with white and brown sugars.
Process on/off with 8 to 10 pulses or until butter and sugar are mixed and then process continuously until mixture is creamed.

title: italian beef
directions: Cut slits in roast in different places.
Cut garlic in halves and place into slits.
Salt and pepper roast and place in large roasting pan.
Mix together Italian seasonings, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Put on top of roast.
Fill pan half to 2/3 with water.
Put bouillon cubes in the water; cover and cook at 325° for 4 1/2 hours.
Remove cover; add peppers and cook, uncovered, 1/2 hour more.
Remove roast from gravy; cool and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, slice meat thinly.
When serving, heat gravy first, then add meat.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Chop pineapple and cherries.
Mix well first 7 ingredients, then add all other ingredients.
Drop teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: congo bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes; cut in bars or squares.

title: laura's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except breadcrumbs and butter; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown breadcrumbs in butter; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening in skillet, add remaining ingredients, except buns.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, adding more tomato juice, if necessary.
Spoon onto split hamburger buns.

title: decorated butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together well.
Add to mixture the remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Press down with a fork. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta pate
directions: Measure 1 cup pasta and cook according to directions.
Cool. Add all ingredients until mixed well.
(Cream cheese mixes better if at room temperature.)
Place in a loaf pan and refrigerate an hour or longer, overnight is even better.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and add.
Add nuts.
Stir to mix and pour into crusts. Chill.

title: michele's potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients in greased casserole until full.
Add milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Mix 1 cup crushed corn flake crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine and sprinkle over chicken.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Combine the oleo, sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Shape into eggs and chill real well.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in a small pan set inside a larger pan of warm water. Dip eggs in chocolate.

title: tomato shake up
directions: Blend or shake all ingredients except nutmeg.
(Add a little milk to thin, if desired.)
Chill.
Serve in chilled mug. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sausage bread
directions: Raise dough.
While dough is rising, saute sausage.
When cooked, drain and cool.
Take risen dough and roll out oblong (not too thin).
Add egg and parsley to sausage.
Scatter over dough, not too close to edge.
Then add grated Mozzarella and grated Romano.
Overlap your sides, then start to roll from long end. Brush with egg yolk on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Combine veggies.
Pour salad dressing over and toss to coat evenly. Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot dog chile
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add all the ingredients.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours.
Serves 25.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain artichoke hearts.
Place 1 artichoke heart on each slice of bread.
Stir together cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on top of each artichoke heart.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes or until the cheese is melted and light golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: calico salad
directions: Cool vegetables and drain thoroughly.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed, mixing well.
Do not let rise.
Cover and place in refrigerator until ready to use. Then roll out dough on lightly floured board to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Again do not let rise.
Have oven heated to 450°.
Bake until brown.
Time depends on the size of the biscuits.

title: angel berry trifle
directions: In a small bowl, whisk the milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes or until thickened.
In a mixing bowl, beat the yogurt, cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in pudding mixture and 1 cup whipped topping.
Place a third of the cake cubes in a 4-quart trifle bowl.
Top with a third of the pudding mixture, a third of the berries and half of the remaining whipped topping.
Repeat layers once.
Top with remaining cake, pudding and berries.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Yield: 14 servings.

title: salmon stew
directions: Put milk and margarine into pot and heat.
When margarine is melted, add salmon, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling and serve with saltines.

title: pickled red onions
directions: Preliminary: Fill a teakettle with water and bring to a boil. Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and peppercorns in a medium-sized bowl and stir until the sugar is dissolved. Place onion slices in a colander in the sink and slowly pour all the boiling water over them. They will wilt slightly. Drain well and transfer to the bowl of marinade.

title: pastitsio
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water, drain and return to pan.
Pour 1/2 of the melted butter over the macaroni.
Add the grated cheese (save a little to sprinkle on the top) and 3 slightly beaten eggs. Set aside.
Prepare meat sauce by frying the onions in a little butter.
Add ground meat and brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomato paste, wine, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/2 of the macaroni in the bottom of a large rectangular baking pan.
Cover entirely with meat.
Spread the rest of the macaroni on top.
Make cream sauce by putting 1/2 of the original butter in medium saucepan, add cornstarch, then milk.
Stir constantly over medium-low heat until slightly thick.
Add salt and remove from heat.
When slightly cooled, add 2 beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour sauce over macaroni and sprinkle with the rest of the grated cheese.

title: creamed new potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and dice.
Melt the butter.
Remove from heat and blend in flour until smooth.
Return to heat; add milk and cream, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the diced potatoes and chives or parsley and heat through.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese into small pieces; melt in microwave until soft.
Add the salsa and milk.
Keep hot in serving dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: karen's dip recipe
directions: Microwave 10 minutes or until set or bake in 350° oven, using the toothpick test.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, heat bell pepper, onion, jalapeno and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until vegies are tender, about 5 minutes.
Add turkey and cook, stirring frequently until
no longer pink.
Add tomato sauce, corn, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the chili powder.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp; set pulp and shells aside.
In a skillet, brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add pulp, bread crumbs, milk and dill.
Spoon into zucchini shells.
Place in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: courting dip (shrimp)
directions: Rinse shrimp in cold water and drain well.
Mash shrimp with fork (however, my pastry cutter works quite well).
Add 1/2 cup of mayonnaise and mix lightly.
Add garlic powder (not garlic salt), then add more of mayonnaise to make it a light dip consistency. Chill, covered, for an hour, if possible.
Serve with chips.

title: no bake applesauce torte
directions: Mix jello with applesauce.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: low-fat tri-color noodle salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder to taste.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add pineapple. Spread cake mix over top.
Pour margarine over cake; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
While the macaroni are cooking, mix the tuna, soup and cheese package.
Add salt, black pepper, and red pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: carrot loaf(a meat substitute)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan until carrots are cooked through.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of cherries, spreading it evenly.
Next, slice butter and dot evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters.
Remove core; shred.
In heavy skillet or Dutch oven, slice pre-frozen bacon into cubes.
Place in cold skillet and fry uncovered until transparent.
Put some of the sliced onion on top of bacon, then add some of the shredded cabbage; toss after approximately 5 minutes.

title: white fluffy icing
directions: Cook milk and flour over medium heat, stirring until mixture becomes thick.
Remove from heat and let cool.
In separate pan, beat oleo and shortening on high for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat 4 more minutes.
Mix in flour mixture and beat 4 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and dip out on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: pepper log(cream spread)
directions: Chop onion and chip beef finely.
Mix in cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.
Roll into a log or ball.
Roll in ground pepper if desired.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.
Great on crackers.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Form into a ball.
Half the ball and put between wax paper and roll out in a 6 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread 1/2 of sausage on each rectangle.
Roll tight and refrigerate until firm.
Slice 1/4-inch pinwheels.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until done at 425°.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of baking dish.
Spread crushed pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pineapple, pecan pieces on top and slice margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Make pudding and refrigerate.
Mix together flour, oleo and pecans.
Press in bottom of glass baking dish or pan.
Brown at 300° about 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: bohemian doughnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out with doughnut cutter.
Drop in hot grease.
Turn over to brown other side.
If you want sweet doughnuts, powder them with confectioners sugar while hot or eat plain.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender (slice with peel on).
Drain well. Season with salt and pepper.

Mix squash, carrots, onions, sour cream, pimentos, margarine, water chestnuts and soup together. Make layer of half the mixture, then half the crumbs, rest of squash mixture, then the rest of the crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Put egg in bottom of cup; beat with fork.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Add all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Roll out.
Makes 2 double crusts or 5 singles.

title: taco dip
directions: *I chop them into a strainer and place in bowl in refrigerator overnight.

title: roast beef with gravy
directions: Cut roast in half; rub with 1/4 cup flour.
Place a 5-quart slow cooker.
In a bowl, combine soup and gravy mixes and remaining flour; stir in water until blended. Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender. Slice roast.
Yes, serve with mashed potatoes and gravy.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender all ingredients.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients; add milk.
Sift together flour, tartar, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and add vanilla.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a very small cookie cutter 2-inches.
Place a teaspoonful of date filling on each cookie and cover with a second cookie; press edges together.
With a fork, punch holes in top of cookie.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 12 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, combine ground beef, Chili-O mix and tomato sauce. Cook yellow rice, add milk to cheese soup to thin.
Layer in pan the beef, rice and soup.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach tart
directions: Mix milk, cheese, lemon juice and pour into cooled crust. Layer peaches in small slices on top.
Cover with peach jello dissolved by package directions.

title: appetizer spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach, then pour boiling water over spinach.
Let it stand for 10 minutes; drain.
Mix with all ingredients and chill overnight.
Roll into balls.
Freeze, then store in plastic bags. Bake from the frozen bags as needed.
(Great for receptions.) Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix sugar, potato flakes and water together in bowl, then pour in starter.
Leave out of refrigerator, uncovered, for 8 to 12 hours.
When bubbly, take out 1 cup to make bread and return to refrigerator.
If not making bread, after feeding starter, give or throw away 1 cup.
Always feed every 3 to 5 days to keep from deflating starter.
When your container gets too full to feed double batch, throw away or give away 1 cup.
I use extra starter in bread; just makes it tastier.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Tie garlic, bay leaves and cloves in double thickness of cheesecloth.
Cut each slab of ribs in half.
Put ribs and spice mixture into oven.
Add cold water to cover and simmer 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Drain.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix salt, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Sprinkle mixture into bottom of pie shell.
Place a thick layer of tomatoes over mixture.
Sprinkle more sugar mixture over top of tomatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Add another layer of tomatoes and mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Dribble 3 tablespoons lemon juice over top.
Add topping.
Bake 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Lower to 350°.
Bake 50 minutes until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Pour hot milk over bread crumbs.
Add butter, cheese, salt to taste and well beaten eggs.
Mix with macaroni.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven for about 40 minutes, or until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the	ingredients
into
a
ball.
Roll in an extra cup of chopped pecans until covered.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: puerto escondido salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl or serving dish. Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil and mix at medium speed until no visible trace of oil.
Mix at least 3 minutes.
Add flour and spices.
Then add pumpkin at a lower speed until the batter is well blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic - german goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and celery over low heat.
Add crushed bay leaf, kidney beans, macaroni and carrots. Mix gently.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 1 serving.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix dry ingredients, then cut in butter. Mix eggs, almond extract and buttermilk.
Pour into flour mixture.
Fold together just until mixed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake until done, 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Add macaroni. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato chip drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and chips.
Stir well until mixed.
Add shortening and milk all at once.
Stir lightly and quickly.
Drop from tablespoon on oiled cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all of first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Serve small slices with syrup drizzled on top. Very rich!

title: ham potato skillet
directions: Brown ham in butter and brown sugar.
Remove ham and pour off drippings.
Mix soup, milk, water, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and carrots; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender, about 35 minutes. Place ham over vegetables.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, spices and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add the well beaten egg.
Mix hot water and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain canned fruit; mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: glossy chocolate icing(this icing is for chocolate lovers.)
directions: Melt, in double boiler, the butter and chocolate.
In separate dish, pour scalding hot milk over powdered sugar and salt, stirring constantly, until completely dissolved.
Add vanilla and stir.
To this add the melted butter and chocolate.
Beat until consistency is smooth and glossy.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with flat side of knife.
Lay a slice of cheese on one end of chicken breast.
Lay the slice of ham on top of the cheese.
Roll chicken breasts so that the cheese and ham are covered.
Secure with toothpicks.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and brown in butter until golden.
Place chicken in casserole.
Heat soup and milk in pan; add sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: hidden valley ranch "spicy" apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a serving dish.
Cover and chill at least one hour before serving.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and cook in sheet pan. While hot, poke full of holes.
Pour condensed milk and cream of coconut into cake.
Chill thoroughly.
When chilled, spread Cool Whip on cake and cover with coconut.

title: rhubarb iced tea
directions: Cut stalks of rhubarb into 3-inch lengths.
Add to water and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Strain the liquid and add sugar. Serve iced with a sprig of mint.

title: tangy citrus punch(nonalcoholic)
directions: Makes 2 medium punch bowls full, 50 cups.
It is a tangy, tart citrus type punch.
Do not leave anything out or it will taste like too much grapefruit.
Very refreshing, often served at lunches.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook the ground round in a skillet until pink.
Add onion and continue cooking until the pink is gone and onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until edges start to turn brown.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken casserole with wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 3-quart baking dish.
Spread rice evenly in bottom of dish.
Top with chicken or turkey. Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Mix soup with milk and pour over top. Add layers of olives and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake, let cool, cut into three parts and then cut into small pieces.
Add one layer of cake, then pineapple, Cool Whip, another layer of cake, cherry pie filling, pudding, another layer of cake and then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except parmesan cheese.
Pour in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle top with the parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix ground beef (uncooked), taco seasoning and refried beans together.
If adding oregano, add into this mixture.
In a baking pan, put a layer of lasagna noodles on the bottom. Top with layer of meat. Make three layers, ending with meat.
Mix salsa and water together and pour over top of last layer.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour on 350°.
Spread sour cream and Cheddar cheese over the top. Then put a few chopped green onions on top.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted (uncovered).
Let stand at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: mince meat pie
directions: Add all the ingredients at once and cook over slow heat until raisins become plump.
Do not add bread crumbs until almost time to remove from heat as it is bad to stick.
This should make two or three pies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Scoop with ice cream scoop.
Flatten bottom.
Put on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Place on tomato slice.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rosie's spoon bread tamale pie bake
directions: Brown hamburger in olive oil.
Add onions, pepper and garlic. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in corn meal mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add olives.
Put in 3-quart casserole (9 x 13-inch). Heat milk, butter/margarine and salt.
Slowly stir in 1/2 cup corn meal.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture.
Refrigerate or bake at 375° (chilled 1 1/2 hours) for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: celery gravy
directions: Lightly brown onion in butter.
In separate pan, combine water and celery and simmer until tender.
When onion is tender, add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly. Add celery and water.
Season to taste and heat thoroughly.
This is great for turkey dressing.

title: very good pie crust mix
directions: Mix flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture is very fine.
Store in covered container, no refrigeration needed.
Makes:

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool and separate meat from bone. Set aside.
Save 3/4 cup broth.
Cook in oleo, onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Boil water; add rice.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well except ham.
Spread on the ham and roll as a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice and put on Ritz crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together all dry ingredients.
In smaller bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Add pecans and strawberries. Add to dry ingredients.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chicken broth or bouillon, then cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cook 2 additional minutes.
Add chicken and pimento and heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: lattice top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can fried onions.
Spread mixture into a greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to serve. Arrange in center of tray and surround with meat cubes for dipping.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick muffins
directions: Mix and bake in moderate oven.
Makes 6.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover pretzel layer. Stir jello into boiling water and add cold water.
While hot, add frozen strawberries and stir until syrupy.
Pour over layers in pan.
Refrigerate.
Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip for garnish.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt together chocolate and margarine over very low heat.
Add to powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat in enough milk until smooth and spreading consistency.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Cook and sweeten apples; add cinnamon to taste.
Mix ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake until done at 325° to 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar and oil.
Beat together.
Add vanilla, soda, flour, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Batter will be thick.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to cool. Frost when cool.

title: essie's cobbler
directions: *Drained berries or peaches from No. 2 can or about 2 cups of fresh fruit (a little more or less); 1/4 to 1 cup sugar and 1 cup fruit juice for canned fruit or 1 cup sugar and 1 cup boiling water for fresh fruit.

title: date delights
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add rice cereal and nuts.
Mix.
Cool and form into balls. Roll in coconut.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces, removing bones.
Mix with lettuce, cauliflower, thin rings of red pepper and/or cucumber and peas.
Pour on French or Italian salad dressing and garnish with bacon slices on top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add pork chops; brown lightly on both sides (8 minutes).
Slightly overlap chops in skillet.
Pour in 1/2 cup apple cider.
Add potatoes in a single layer along with white part of green onions.
Sprinkle with sage, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion for 3 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add carrots and soup mixture with zucchini and onions. Melt oleo and mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add vegetables.
Put rest of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel apple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place 1 1/4 cups of apple pie filling in a saucepan.
Divide the remaining apple pie filling and place half in each pie crust.
Beat sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour half of mixture into each pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool cakes to room temperature, about one hour.
Drizzle caramel topping and remaining apple pie filling over cooled cheesecake and garnish with pecan halves.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots (medium size slices, not too thin). Boil carrots until tender; drain.
Slice onion into thin slices; cut bell pepper into strips.
Mix onion, pepper and all other ingredients (except carrots) together.
Pour this mixture into pot with drained carrots; bring to a boil.
Cool a little and refrigerate.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Beat eggs for 4 minutes.
Add cake mix, oil and mandarin oranges.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: easy stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef with onions. Layer cabbage on bottom of 9 x 13 Pyrex baking dish. Add ground meat mixed with dry rice on top of cabbage. Add soup with 1 can of water. Top with Parmesan cheese (tall thin can). Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: coconut macaroon cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk, coconut and coconut flavoring.
Pour in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat until stiff.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Use wire whip to mix and then when smooth, use wooden spoon to stir.

title: tuna mousse
directions: In a blender put boiling water, gelatin and onion and blend. Add sour cream and salad dressing.
Slowly add tuna.
While it is blending, don't let it get too liquified.
Put in a 2 1/2 cup mold and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Then reduce heat to 350° and bake until filling is firm (about 30 minutes).

title: cantaloupe marmalade
directions: Mix cantaloupe, oranges and lemon juice and boil mixture 15 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon and orange peels.
Cook mixture over high heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sausage lentil soup
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; drain fat.
Crumble sausage and put in a crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients except mustard.
Cook on high for 3 hours or on low for 5 hours, or until the vegetables and lentils are tender.
Stir in mustard and remove bay leaf before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on toast cutouts or crackers. Broil until bubbly.
Serve hot.
Makes 30.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cereal raisin cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat margarine until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in cereal and raisins. Drop by level tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in microwave.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Press into a 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Will look doughy, but do not overcook.
Makes 24 bars.

title: aunt mae's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender (reserve 2 cups of broth).
Melt margarine in broth.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Strip chicken into pieces; put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread soup mixture over chicken.
Spread stuffing over the top of the soup mixture.
Pour broth over the top of this.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's pickled beets
directions: I add one teaspoon of nutmeg.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh pineapple, strawberries, apple slices, etc.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually until thick.
Add cream, milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and freeze.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown floured chicken in shortening.
Place in baking dish. Add all other ingredients to skillet.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour in covered dish in 350° oven.
Add 1 pound cooked shrimp the last 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Beat in egg and egg whites.
Add yogurt and mix well.
Blend dry ingredients separately, then stir into batter.
Add vanilla.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups which have been sprayed with nonstick coating spray.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in baking dish. Can be topped with 2 cups crushed potato chips. Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook, drain and cool carrots.
Boil soup, sugar, oil, vinegar and spices.
Put in a 2-quart casserole with carrots, onion and peppers.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: strawberry squares
directions: For crumb mixture, combine flour, nuts, margarine and brown sugar.
Spread into a baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, stir.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine egg whites, strawberries, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix until creamy.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the whip cream until smooth.
Combine both mixtures together. Spoon evenly over crumbs in baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Cover.
Freeze at least 6 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Doritos and dressing.
When ready to serve, add Doritos and dressing (enough to coat), then toss.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in one mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish (pan) and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: graham cracker cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain off grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup, green beans, salt and a little milk.
Heat in baking dish.
Serve.

title: mexican mushrooms
directions: In mixing bowl, toss together Cheddar cheese, sour cream, chopped green onions, cilantro, Mexican blend seasoning, green chiles and vegetable oil.
Mix well and set aside.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir together flour and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make out biscuits and place in pan.
Let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake until golden brown (approximately 45 minutes to one hour).
Top with instant pudding (vanilla or lemon flavor).

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in a little oil.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and tomatoes.
Add a little water and flour to thicken.
Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: curried beef or chicken
directions: Brown the garlic and onion in oil until tender, then add the brown sugar, ginger, water, curry powder and cornstarch.
Add tomatoes last, and only heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: simple salsa
directions: Mix tomatoes, chillies and onions together.
Chill overnight or 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: moonlite bar-b-q inn's pork and beans
directions: Place beans in baking dish.
Mix in onion, dry mustard, brown sugar and ketchup.
Lay bacon on top of beans.
Bake in 350° oven until bacon is done (30 to 40 minutes).

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water until done.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: celebration cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and cinnamon, mixing thoroughly.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch nonstick pan.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. In bowl, combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar, sour cream and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on top of crust.
Bake on middle rack until set, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: impossible pie
directions: Use blender button.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Grease and flour 10-inch pie pan.
Pour mix into pie pan and bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
It is so nice it makes it's own crust.

title: baked spiced pears
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Peel pear and cut in half, lengthwise. Butter baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Place pears cut side down.
Add seasonings and honey.
Bake 20 minutes. Remove and pour cream and return to oven for 15 minutes. Serve hot, topped with ice cream.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Set aside 2 tablespoons of cheese for top.
In skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter and saute scallions and mushrooms, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Melt remaining butter and saute shrimp and scallops that have been cut into bite size pieces. Stir frequently. Drain. Add to mushroom mixture.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour seafood mixture evenly in pie shell. Add egg mixture. Top with cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli according to package directions. Saute onion and celery in small amount of fat in skillet.
Combine onion, celery, rice, broccoli and butter.
Melt Cheez Whiz in soup with 1/2 cup water in large saucepan.
Stir in broccoli mixture. Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: mixed greens
directions: Wash meats and put
in	large
pot and cook for 45 minutes. Cover with	water.	Clean
greens
well.
Cut
up
and combine with meat.	Season	to
taste.
Put a dash of sugar if desired. Cook over medium
heat for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook first three ingredients until tender.
Cook chicken until tender and cut in small pieces.
Add all ingredients to chopped chicken.
Cook 7 1/2 ounces Ronco spaghetti and drain.
Add to chicken. Mix well.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Add cheese to top.
Put back in oven for about 5 or 10 minutes more.

title: zoe's hot dog casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and tomatoes in microwave for 30 to 50 minutes (time depends on the amount of potatoes used), stirring every 20 minutes.
When the potatoes are cooked, add hot dogs and cheese and heat again until cheese is melted and casserole is warmed through.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until clear.
Crumble cornbread in and stir in sage.
Crumble slices of bread and add to mixture.
Put into baking dish and add enough water to moisten and dot with additional butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: me-maw's poppy seed bread or muffins
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for bread loaf or 25 minutes for mini muffins.

title: baked manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pour 1/3 of jar of spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill manicotti with cheese mixture.
Arrange in pan; pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: texas yum yum cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
The crust will be white when it comes out.
Cool it.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook rice by directions on package. Add remaining ingredients. Put in baking dish and top the mixture with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Take rice off stove and add oleo and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs, sugar and raisins.
Return to stove and add the cans of milk, one at a time.
Bring to a boil and remove from stove.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: angela kennecke's low-fat lazy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown turkey in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add spices and onion.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; reduce to low heat.
Combine Ricotta cheese and sour cream in medium bowl; blend well.
Spoon 1/3 of the meat sauce into baking dish.
Layer 4 uncooked lasagna noodles and 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture on top.
Cover with blend of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Add another layer of meat sauce and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers of noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese. Top with remaining cheese.
Carefully add water to baking dish, pouring around edges of dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for one hour.
