Uncover and bake for 20 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage and spinach.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, half and half, sugar, vinegar and pepper until well blended.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss lightly to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tanya's raspberry cookies
directions: In a large bowl beat sugar, butter, salt and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Using teaspoonful of dough shape into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
With thumb or spoon, make imprint in center of cookies. Bake at 350° for 12 to 16 minutes or until bottom edges are golden brown.
Carefully press imprint again immediately after removal from oven.
Cool on wire rack.
After cooled, fill each cookie with raspberry jelly.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: jewel salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to each package of jello and 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix and put each color into separate pan or bowl. Let harden and cut into small squares.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with cooking oil.
Bake at 300° until thick.

title: country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight.
Clean thoroughly.
Place ham in a large container and cover with cold water.
Put in an apple and an onion, big if the ham is big, small if small.
Pour in molasses and pickling spices.
Simmer very slowly.
Allow 20 minutes per pound.
Remove from heat just before the meat leaves the bone. Let the ham remain in the water until it has cooled.
Remove it later, skin and cut off fat.
Place the trimmed ham in a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and Worcestershire.
Drain pineapple and cut into halves, forming crescents.
Spread the brown sugar over the ham.
Place pineapple halves in rows over brown sugar, piercing each slice with cloves.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes or until sugar glaze browns.

title: cauliflower a la curry
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan and blend in flour.
Add the milk slowly and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Add the curry powder and remove from heat.
Separate the cauliflower into flowerets and cook in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place alternate layers of cauliflower, cheese sauce and cracker crumbs in a greased baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: tuna balls
directions: Mix together until well-blended.
Then work into balls. You may put parsley on top.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook the raisins or fruit cocktail in the water until water is gone.
Cool then add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Mix well; add vanilla and mix.
Pour in well-greased cake pan and bake in 350° oven until done.
Note:
May use 1 cup raisins and 1 cup fruit cocktail.

title: party cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions, adding 1/2 teaspoon Kool-Aid before beating.
Pour into muffin tins greased or paper-lined 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix rest of Kool-Aid into frosting and frost cooled cupcakes.
Makes 24 cupcakes with frosting.

title: hearty nachos
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat; drain. Stir in soup mix, black beans and salsa. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes or until heated through. Arrange tortilla chips on serving platter. Spread beef mixture over chips; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top, if desired, with sliced green onions, sliced pitted ripe olives, chopped tomatoes and chopped cilantro.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Fold in the apples and walnuts. Pour in greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 1889 chicago's world's fair, hazel dubberly's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour and spices together; add alternately with buttermilk to the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add jam.
(All of this can be mixed with an electric mixer.)
Chop dates, figs and cherries; add to mixture, along with the chopped nuts.
(This makes the mixture too heavy to use the electric mixer.)
Bake in layers in a 350° oven until done.
Remove from pans immediately.
Fill with Fruit Cake Filling.
This makes 2 cakes, one with four 9-inch layers and one with four 8-inch layers.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drop sliced banana in pineapple juice with 2 teaspoons Fruit-Fresh dissolved. Mix all fruits together.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange jello with Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce with Ritz crackers.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Combine pecans and coconut and put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on package and pour over pecan and coconut mixture.
Melt in saucepan 1 stick of butter.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar; heat until mixed thoroughly.
Pour over top of cake batter.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: crunchtop chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts (boil until tender), break into bite-size pieces, and place in a 3-quart oblong greased casserole dish. Cover with Swiss cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Melt butter, add to stuffing and spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour, or until top looks crusty.
Easy and taste!

title: baked beans
directions: Parboil beans until soft.
Pour off excess water and place beans in crock.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook in oven at 300° until very soft, 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together oatmeal, 1 stick margarine and boiling water, let cool. Then add white sugar and 1 cup brown sugar. Add eggs, flour, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350°

for 35 - 40 minutes. Next melt 1 stick margarine add sugar and evaporated milk, let come to boil. Remove from heat and add coconut, pecans and vanilla and pour over hot cake and broil. Watch closely while under broiler as cake will scorch easily.

title: real mexican nachos
directions: Spread a thin layer of refried beans onto tortilla chips, then top with chiles and shredded cheese.
Bake at 450° until bubbly, about 5 minutes.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until about 5 tablespoons liquid remains.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in cooled liquid and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats and cooked raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix Crisco oil, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rocky mountain baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole.
Bake covered at 325° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Uncover the last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serves 20.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon strips, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Mix onions with potatoes. Mix soup (do not dilute), melted oleo and sour cream. Stir into potato and onions. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Remove. Add shredded cheese on top of casserole. Return to oven. Bake 1/2 hour more at 350°. Serves 12.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Then add rest and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mustard fried fish
directions: Combine sour cream and mustard.
Coat fish or fillets with mixture and let stand for 20 minutes.
Season cornmeal with salt and pepper.
Dredge fish in cornmeal mixture and deep fry in hot oil until browned.

title: fat-free shortcake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, cornstarch, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Mix the egg whites, milk, corn syrup and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Stir all until smooth.
Pour into a sprayed 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and remove from pan.
Cut into squares or cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Split halves and add prepared strawberries or other fruit with juice.
(Prepare fruit with artificial sweetener ahead to make natural juice or minimal sugar.)
Makes 9 (3 x 3-inch) servings. Each serving plus fruit equals 200 calories, 3 grams protein, 48 grams carbohydrates, 0.9 fat, 0 cholesterol and 170 milligrams sodium.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar. Mix in oleo. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: aunt ruth's deer chili
directions: Cover meat with water 1-inch above meat.
Cook slow until tender.
When half done (30 to 40 minutes), add remaining ingredients and cook until done.
May need more or less extras. Taste and adjust.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Set aside.
Put water and butter on stove until butter is melted.
Bring to a boil.
Then pour water/butter into flour mixture.
Mix together.
Set aside or refrigerate until cool, then knead and roll out and cut, then add to boiling broth.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; mix remaining ingredients with the spinach, saving 1/2 can of onion rings.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle remaining onion rings on top.

title: simply delicious dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions (use 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan).
Cool cake in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken 'n' rice(for microwave)
directions: Mix together soup and milks.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture with rice, mushrooms, 1/4 package of onion soup mix and pimento.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cover with waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Cook on Full Power for 4 minutes.
Place chicken breasts on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 package onion soup mix.
Cover with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Cook on Full power for 15 to 18 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Turn chicken over 1 to 2 times during cooking time.

title: strawberry dip for fruit
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, blend
all ingredients with a wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: bran busters
directions: Split and toast English muffins.
Spread with softened butter. Put a slice of pineapple or slices of banana and a little honey on each.
Broil until topping is lightly browned.

title: savory spareribs and cabbage
directions: Wash spareribs in cold water.
Place ribs in a pot and cover with water.
Add onions, garlic, bay leaves, salt, pepper and thyme.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and cover pot.
Simmer meat for 40 to 50 minutes or until fork-tender.
Heat oven to 450°. Remove meat from pot and place in a baking pan.
Add cabbage and potatoes to the pan that the meat was cooked in.
(Do not throw away the juices.)

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix with sugar and beaten eggs.
Add coconut and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake in 350° oven until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, oleo, brown sugar and pecans. Sprinkle in a large sheet cake pan and bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Thaw peas; combine with eggs and onion in bowl.
Cut broccoli stems into small pieces, flowerets into same size as peas or small pieces.
Add with peas to bowl.
Mix mayo and sour cream.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Toss; refrigerate briefly.

title: halibut
directions: Mix wine and salt.
Marinate fish in mixture for 1 to 2 hours. Drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Dip both sides of halibut in bread crumbs.
Arrange fillets side by side in greased baking dish.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread evenly over fish.
Spread thin layer of bread crumbs.
Dust with paprika. Bake in hot oven at 500° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes. Serve with lemon.
Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until brown.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add corn, eggs and 1 cup of the cracker crumbs. Place in oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs; dot with additional 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until center is firm and top is browned.

title: weight watchers chicken loaf
directions: Mix vegetables, chicken, seasonings, mustard and mayonnaise together.
Dissolve bouillon in 1 cup boiling water and dissolve gelatin in remaining 1/2 cup of cold water.
Add gelatin to boiling bouillon.
Add bouillon to mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: no fail brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Mix all other ingredients together.
Add the melted butter to your mixture.
Pour contents into baking pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: glazed carrots and apples
directions: In a frying pan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the carrots, apples and ginger.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes.
Add the sugar, orange zest and juice and salt.
Cook, stirring, until the carrots and apples are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix yogurt, butter, egg, lemon peel and vanilla.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add yogurt mixture; stir just to combine. Stir in blueberries.

title: chocolate cookies(no baking needed)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the butter, milk, chocolate syrup, sugar and salt.
Put the saucepan on the stove over medium heat and stir until the mixture is mixed well.
Bring to a boil and then remove the pan from the heat. Add the rolled oats, vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts.
Put waxed paper onto cookie sheets. Drop the batter from a teaspoon onto the waxed paper. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crock-pot sausages
directions: Bake sausages for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Slice the sausages into 1-inch pieces. Put in crock-pot.
Add mushrooms and pepper salad, mix.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours on low setting.

title: brunch punch
directions: Mix strawberry jello, sugar, and hot water and mix until dissolved. Add cold water and blend. Add orange juice, and pineapple juice and chill overnight. Add ice cream right before serving. Pour ginger ale over ice cream.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Make 3 wells.
Put oil, vinegar and vanilla in each well.
Pour cold water over all and mix with fork.
Don't beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with favorite topping.

title: twice baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes and remove all pulp.
Use pulp in another dish, such as mashed potatoes.
With scissors, cut the potato skins in strips about an inch or so wide.

Put on a baking sheet; brush generously with melted butter and season with salt, freshly ground black pepper (if desired) and a little Tabasco sauce (optional) and put in a 450° to 475° oven or under the broiler until they get brown and crisp to your taste. Serve with a beverage, as an appetizer.
I think these are better than potato chips.

title: continental chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to make gravy-like mixture.

Fold chicken breasts in half, wrapping one piece of bacon and 2 slices of dried beef around each, holding together with 2 toothpicks. Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish, pouring gravy mixture over them.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Can even be made in crock-pot.
Serve over rice.

title: scones
directions: After a trip to Scotland, my sister, Sue Fore, raved about scones with marmalade.
I began searching for recipes.
This is a good basic recipe, my favorite is Scottish Oat.
Scones are sort of an Old World cousin to our Southern biscuit.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add salt, pepper and wine. Cook about 5 minutes over medium heat. Add tomatoes and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil. Then add cheese; stir in. Cook about 1 hour (simmer). Add fresh basil last 10 minutes. Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight, if possible.

title: baba ghanouy
directions: Make tiny cuts in the flesh side of the eggplant.
Sprinkle it with salt and set on a plate for 30 minutes.
Rinse the eggplant with water and pat it dry.
Heat the broiler.
Brush the cut sides with oil and broil the eggplant as close to the element as possible for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Move the eggplant to about 6 inches from the element and continue broiling for 20 minutes or until very tender when tested with a fork.
Leave to cool.

title: sandy's corn pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch, milk, corn, sugar and eggs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg, vanilla and milk. Stir in dry ingredients. Roll into balls and roll in extra sugar. Bake at 375° until edges brown.
While cookies cool, press a kiss firmly into each cookie until edges crack.

title: fresh mushroom stuffing
directions: Prepare corn bread, using package directions.
Cool and crumble.
Toss in large bowl with bread cubes; set aside.
Cook bacon crisp; drain.
Add mushrooms, celery and onion to bacon drippings; cook about 10 minutes.
Crumble bacon into bread mixture.
Add vegetables with giblet broth.
Stir and make moist stuffing.
Makes enough for 10 to 20-pound turkey.

title: teriyaki glaze for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until thick and bubbly.
Brush on ribs during last 15 minutes of grilling.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: all american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and butter or margarine with apples and lemon juice.
Place in unbaked pie shell; dot with additional butter or margarine.
Place remaining pie shell on top.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Stir in large saucepan on top of stove the cornmeal, hot water, sugar, salt, margarine and milk.
Cook over medium-high heat until well blended, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Blend in beaten eggs.
Cook to a full boil, reduce heat to medium and cook for 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or large cast-iron skillet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Spread 1 tablespoon of margarine on top.
Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: tartlets
directions: Cream the margarine and cream cheese thoroughly. Add and blend well the flour.
Press a small amount of dough into tart pans. Chilling the dough a little makes the dough handle easier.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Put the chopped tomatoes in a strainer set over a large bowl; place the bowl in the refrigerator and let the tomatoes drain for at least 30 minutes.

title: "chicken" loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake in large, flat pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good cold, sliced for sandwiches.

title: kentucky fried apples
directions: With your paring knife, peel a 1 1/2-inch strip around the center of the apple.
This band will remove about a third of the apple peel.
Cut the apple in quarters.
Next, slice each quarter into 3 or 4 sections.

title: oatmeal refrigerator shortbread cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, then add flour, salt and oats.
Divide dough in half and shape each half into a roll about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour or longer.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 13 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sausage 'n pepper braid
directions: Brown sausage and cook pepper until done, stirring to break up meat; drain.
Cool.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl. Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, seasoning, margarine, 1 egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; divide into 6 pieces.
Roll each into 14 x 4-inch strips.
Stir cheese into sausage; spoon down center of each strip.
Pinch long edges together to form 14-inch ropes; seal.
Braid 3 ropes together; seal.
Repeat.
Place on greased baking sheet, cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Beat remaining egg and brush on loaves.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pepper steak(serves 2 or 4 people as a main course)
directions: Marinate steak in the next 6 ingredients.
Toss with forks and let stand up to 6 hours.

title: open-faced sandwiches
directions: On each slice of bread, place 1 slice of cheese, then tomato slice, then onion slice, then pepper slice. Top with 2 to 3 half slices of bacon.
Place under broiler until bacon is cooked.

title: murbes' gumbo(necessity is the mother of invention)
directions: No salt or fat is needed.

title: tea ring
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Scald the milk and add the shortening.
Let cool slightly before adding to flour mixture.
Add the egg and flour.
Add more flour as needed and knead.
Let rise.
Roll out to oblong shape (on floured surface).
Spread melted butter over rolled out surface.
On top, sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll up in circle.
Cut every 3-inches and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: banana upside-down cake
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter and add 2/3 cup sugar and slice bananas and add nuts.
Mix other ingredients.
Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add 2 egg yolks and vanilla.
Alternately add dry and milk ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour over bananas.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: noodle salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bone and skin chicken.
Add salt and carrots in a large pot with 2 quarts water.
Cook until tender.
Add peas and enough water to make 2 quarts of broth.
Bring to boil.
Add dumplings.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Set aside 10 minutes.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 muffins.

title: quick peach crisp
directions: Spoon can of peach or apple pie filling into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microcook, covered, on 100%
(High) for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
To each serving, add 3 tablespoons of granola and a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and put in buttered shallow baking dish.

title: twin angel food party pies
directions: Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.
Cut cake in half horizontally with serrated knife.
Place on serving plates with cut sides up.
Cut around cake 1 1/2-inches from outer edge, down 3/4-inch and through to center.
Gently pull out cut cake 1 1/2-inches wide rim.
Fill center hole with removed cake. Repeat for second half.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon pepper marinade.
Cook with lid on for about 1 hour.
When tender, take out, remove skin and cut up.
Cut celery very fine.
Mix in salad dressing and mayonnaise.
You can add a little more salt, pepper and several dashes of red pepper.

title: cindy burkholder layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over melted butter sprinkle graham cracker crumbs.
Over the top of that sprinkle coconut. Over that sprinkle chocolate chips.
Over that sprinkle butterscotch chips.
Over that sprinkle walnuts, then pour milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant; boil in small amount of water on low heat until tender.
Drain and mash; add cubed cheese, salt, pepper, egg and crushed Ritz crackers.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Top with sliced cheese to cover. Add butter pat and bake in 375 degree oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put in greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over ingredients.
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind apples and cranberries.
Put sugar in them and set aside while fixing the other ingredients.
Mix all together and freeze. Take out and cut in squares about 30 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine flour, margarine, sugar, cinnamon and baking soda. Put half of the crumb mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread applesauce on top.
Put remaining crumb mixture on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hominy and sour cream
directions: Drain hominy.
Place in pan on burner with margarine. Sprinkle generously with garlic salt, simmer.
Remove from heat and add sour cream and green chilies.
Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° until bubbly.
Great as a side dish with Mexican food.

title: pinwheels(for kids)
directions: Spray (2 to 3 short sprays) 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread in bottoms and sides of pan with paper towel.
Mix gelatin and water in 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir to dissolve completely.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together soups and 1 soup can of milk.
Pour soup
mixture over hamburger. Layer Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer: 1/2 angel food cake, crumbled; pineapple, partially drained; strawberry pie filling; Cool Whip and chopped pecans. Then repeat layer.

title: turkey cantonese
directions: Saute onion in butter; add turkey.
Add pineapple juice and vinegar and simmer 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water chestnut juice.
Pour into skillet and cook until thick.
Add pineapple tidbits, tomatoes, water chestnuts and salt; simmer. Serve over rice.
Serves 8.
(Good way to use leftover Thanksgiving turkey.)

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine ingredients, adding well beaten eggs last.
Pour into pan in which butter has been melted. Stir until heated and put into oven.
Stir occasionally as potatoes brown on sides and top. Bake at 350° until light brown and firm.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and drop in skillet by spoonfuls in hot oil.
Fry until brown on each side.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare the Shortcrust Pastry as directed.
It is especially good (for this pie) if you use only lemon juice and Marsala instead of water to moisten it.
Line a 10-inch pie dish and roll out a top crust.

title: belgium potatoes
directions: Cut based potatoes into one inch cubes.
Heat butter in large pan until just simmering. Add the potatoes, add salt and pepper. Brown potatoes on all sides, add chives and serve warm.
Add parsley for garnish.
About 6 servings.

title: steak over rice
directions: Cut
steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in
oil using high heat.
Add onions; saute until tender and crisp.
Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and soy sauce. Pour
over
steak.
Add
mushrooms; reduce heat, cover and
simmer for
1 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: old-fashion chicken and dumplins
directions: Put water, onion, celery, pepper, 1 teaspoon salt and fryer in Dutch oven.
Cook chicken.
Let cool; remove fat from broth. Combine flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out, kneading lightly 4 to 5 times.
Pat dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Pinch off 1 1/2-inch pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mama's veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a microwaveproof casserole, sprayed with Pam.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin; stir and cool.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture into a mold; refrigerate until congealed.
Spread with sour cream and top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; season to taste and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Mix sugar and flour together and add to eggs. Melt butter and add to egg mixture. Blend in buttermilk. Pour into pie crust. Grate nutmeg evenly on top of pie and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until medium brown and center of pie is set.

title: beef and green peppers(international cuisine japanese)
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil at high heat.
Saute green pepper slices.
Sprinkle on 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon Accent. Fry 2 minutes, then remove to a platter.
Fry pieces of meat in small amounts until medium rare (2 to 3 minutes).
Add vegetables to meat and mix well.
Add 2 cups water and 4 teaspoons soy sauce to 6 teaspoons cornstarch.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Stir until thick.
Serve over plain white rice.
Serves four people.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; rinse in cold water.
Saute onions in oil until clear.
Add chopped chilies.
Add meat (sausage and beef mixed) slowly; cook until browned.
Add soup, corn, olives and mushrooms.
Use all liquids.
Cook together until all ingredients are well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 of the cheese, grated.
Mix with spaghetti.
Pour the mixture into large baking dishes.
Top with cheese; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This recipe makes enough to feed the entire church (if Eddy's out of town).
I'm exaggerating, but it does make lots!

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook in a pan on stove.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook 8 hours on high.
Take off lid for last 1/2 hour cooking.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler and heat until cheese and butter are melted. Slice rolls in halves and spread with melted mixture. Place on cookie sheet and broil until light brown. Serve hot.

title: burger bean cup
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Divide into 4 to 6 mounds.
Flatten into circles.
Turn up edge of meat to form a 1/2-inch rim.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining soup and beans.
Spoon into burger cups. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese to soften.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans. Chill in refrigerator.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Drain the pineapple, oranges and cottage cheese well.
Mix together; sprinkle the dry Jell-O over the fruit.
Stir well. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Let chill before serving.
Do not substitute crushed pineapple for chunk.

title: kate's chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice by directions on box.
Saute onion in margarine. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole and heat for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: michael's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure and put into mixing bowl, the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Sift the flour; measure.
Add soda and salt; sift all again.
Add to shortening mixture; add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet; bake 8 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mash potato donuts
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in mashed potatoes.
Mix 3 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; mix in.
Add more flour, if needed (up to 5 cups).
Dough should be stiff.
Roll 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick, cut out and cook in deep fryer.
Makes about 40 to 50 donuts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: My sweet potato, do you carrot for me?
You are the apple of my eye with your radish hair and turnip nose.
My heart beets for you.
My love for you is as strong as onions.
If we cantaloupe, lettuce marry, and we will be a happy pear.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook and mash potatoes.
Add the sour cream, salt, dash of pepper, sugar and margarine.
Add enough milk to bring to proper consistency and beat until fluffy.
Add dill seed, chopped chives and cooked spinach.
Place in greased casserole and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.
Or double recipe and freeze part.

title: mexican seven layer dip
directions: Empty bean dip into a bowl.
In a separate bowl mash avocados, lemon juice and seasonings to taste.
Layer on the top of bean dip.
For 3rd layer, mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of avocados.
Add green onions, tomatoes, cheese and then black olives.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and buttermilk.
Bring just to a boil, then add sifted sugar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.

title: taco salad
directions: Simmer the ground beef, kidney beans and taco seasoning for 10 minutes.
Chop the lettuce, tomatoes and onion into small pieces. Mix all above with the crushed chips, cheese and dressing.
Serve immediately with salsa or sour cream.
Serves 12 (or 6 with Eddy!).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain canned pineapple.
Mix thoroughly the flour and sugar together.
Mix pineapple with flour and sugar mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Crumble 1 pack of Town House crackers or Ritz crackers into margarine.
Sprinkle on top of pineapple.
Bake for 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: chocolate party mix
directions: Mix all together; pour melted chocolate over all and turn onto waxed paper until cool. Break apart and enjoy. Do not seal in container.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Add these to the flour and sift together, 1 teaspoon soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: three bean chili
directions: Cook celery in 1/2 cup water in frypan.
When water is gone, fry hamburger in chunks.
Add onion so it partially cooks.
Add rest of ingredients, including water. Bring to a boil.

title: yellow squash puffs(kids love this.)
directions: Cook squash in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain; mash enough squash to measure 2 cups.
Reserve any leftover for use in other recipes.
Combine 2 cups squash with egg.
Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt; stir well. Add squash mixture and onions; stir until blended.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning only once.

title: dough for dumplings
directions: Make into a roll; stretch up to your wrist.
Dip a tablespoon in hot water and cut off the dumplings, about 12.
Put on a tight-fitting top and let boil 20 minutes before removing the top. If for chicken soup, leave out the sugar.
It may be used for fruit (berries, peaches, etc.).
Requires at least 1 quart of boiling liquid with fruit.
Do not raise lid until done.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and onions.
Drain grease and add Worcestershire sauce, sugar, catsup, mustard and mushroom soup.
Heat and serve over steamed rice.

title: mom's potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until bubbles in middle.
May also be topped with crushed potato chips.
Serves 12.

title: dressing
directions: Cook butter, liver and gizzard together in small frying pan. Cut up celery and onions.
Mix together with the bread crumbs, sage, salt, pepper and milk to your taste.

title: banana fruit bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix well.
Add eggs, mix well then add mashed banana, flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture, a little at a time, then add chocolate chips, cherries, nuts and some cherry juice (1/4 cup).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish-style tuna salad
directions: Toss salad greens, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops and apple bake
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
In 10-inch baking dish, combine beans and cinnamon.
Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine sugar and cloves.
Top pork chops with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix and store until needed.
(Gets better the longer it sits in refrigerator.)

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Skin chicken breasts and cut each into 6 or 8 pieces. Marinate overnight in buttermilk, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Roll in flour and fry in deep fat for 12 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers either with or without peeling left on.
Mix in separate bowl milk, Miracle Whip and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers; mix until cukes are well coated.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours to allow cukes to weep, before serving.

title: lemon-garlic olives
directions: Drain olives, reserving liquid.
Layer half of the olives and next 4 ingredients in olive jar.
Repeat layers.
Pour lemon juice into jar. Add enough reserved olive liquid to fill jar. Screw on lid.
Chill at least 8 hours. Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Yields about 32 appetizer servings.

title: sweet-sour stew
directions: Combine flour, the first teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.

title: chicken sicilian style
directions: Cut up chicken.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup oil.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil.
Cook 1/2 hour more until golden brown.
May add peas if desired.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk; beat until combined.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell. If desired, sprinkle with coarsely chopped peanuts.
Cover; chill in the freezer for at least 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Cook 20 minutes with water and ham. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with crackers of your choice.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender. Mix the soup and milk, set aside.
Place a layer of potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of grated cheese and a layer of soup mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice the boiled potatoes and arrange in layers in a buttered dish, alternating with brown sugar and dots of butter and orange slices.
Add just enough water to make a thick syrup.
Good served with ham or game.

title: savory italian asparagus(low-fat and low-sodium)
directions: To prepare asparagus for cooking, hold the base of the stalk and snap off the end where it seems to break naturally.
The end removed is the tough part.
The remaining stalk should be tender after cooking.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Cover and cook in small amount of boiling water 4 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain.
Arrange on serving platter and keep warm.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Pour croutons on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Brown sausage and onion and add to the top of that.
Then break up broccoli and add all over that; put cheese on top.
Beat egg and milk and pour evenly all over top.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Dump pineapple in pan and spread evenly.
Dump blueberry pie filling evenly on top of the pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on this.
Sprinkle on pecans. Drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery until tender.
Cook rice with water and salt for 14 minutes (until done).
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in Jell-O until smooth.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and salt; stir until mixed. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until candy reaches 245° (about 12 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In a large saucepan mix Velveeta cheese, garlic powder, tomato juice, green chilies and jalapeno peppers.
Melt over low heat; then add hamburger.
Serve hot, room temperature or cold with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Store in refrigerator.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla. Add eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Last, stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and juice; mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and soda; stir into mixture.
Mix crushed pineapple into mixture, then mix in the oatmeal.
Let dough stand 30 minutes before dropping by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen; standing time allows the oatmeal to absorb the juice.

title: crab and shrimp stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and halve them. Scoop out and mash potatoes while still hot, adding first the butter and then other ingredients and mix well. Refill potato skins and bake for 20 minutes at 400°. Garnish with parsley.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in eggs; put in baking dish. Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers two times, ending with pudding mixture.
Chill thoroughly and garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake Duncan Hines cake mix in two 9-inch pans according to instructions on cake mix box; bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp cobbler(apple cobbler never lasts long in our household.)
directions: Lightly butter a baking dish and place apple slices inside. (Apples may be peeled and sliced, or sliced with the skins on.) Sprinkle salt over apples.

title: pickle relish
directions: Place all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix with cake cubes and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together strawberries, glaze and sugar.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Chill.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Chop the cabbage into bite sized pieces and parboil in 1 cup of water for 10 minutes in a covered pan. Drain off water. Make a white sauce by melting the butter and adding the flour and mixing well. Add milk. Cool until thick. Add the salt and pepper. Pour a little of the white sauce in a buttered casserole. Put the cabbage over the sauce. Pour the remainder of the sauce over the cabbage. Top with grated cheese. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sesame shrimp with angel hair pasta
directions: Bring water to boil for pasta.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Cook pasta.
In saucepan combine ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, chutney, seeds and chilies.
Simmer for 3 minutes. Whisk rice vinegar into sauce.
Add shrimp and cook for 8-10 minutes.
Spoon shrimp and sauce over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: play dough
directions: Heat all ingredients until thick.
Cool.
Knead.
Add coloring.
Good project to let kids help make their own play things.

title: banana pudding(lo-cal)
directions: Mix pudding with milk, using hand mixer. Add all of the Cool Whip. Use a large, deep bowl because this makes a lot of banana pudding. Put a small amount of pudding in bottom of bowl. Then put a layer of vanilla wafers. Slice bananas over crackers. Put another layer of wafers over bananas and top with 1/2 of the pudding. Start your layers over and use the remaining ingredients, ending with pudding mixture. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: double-crusted taco pie
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco mix; follow package directions. Place one can of crescents in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Press perforations together.
Crumble seasoned beef on top of crescents.
Add shredded cheese and chopped vegetables.
Top with the second can of crescents.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate and water.
Bring to a boil and stir until chocolate melts; cool.
Stir in vanilla and set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg yolks one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate mixture; beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured (or sprayed with Pam) 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire rack.
Spread Coconut-Pecan Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Yields 1 (3-layer) cake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and milk; bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Spread in buttered pan and cut.

title: steven's favorite poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, poppy seed, soup and chicken. Butter a casserole dish and line it with half the Ritz cracker crumbs. Add chicken mixture; pour margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: freezer punch
directions: Blend all in blender and freeze.
Thaw 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving time and add a 2-liter Sprite (chilled).
Mix and serve.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Make in 3 layers using a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: christmas potpourri
directions: Spices should all be ground.

title: ham slices
directions: Spread each ham slice with a thin coating of mustard.
Place in skillet; pour in wine vinegar.
Cook quickly, turning often until browned.
Place ham on hot platter or plate.
In skillet, add brown sugar to the remaining mustard and vinegar.
Pour in cooking sherry and bring to a boil; pour over ham.
Serves 6.

title: ossie's custard
directions: Scald milk over medium-low heat in a heavy bottom saucepan. Keep milk under boiling stage, stirring so as not to stick.
Mix slightly beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Add half cup of hot liquid to egg mixture.
Stir.
Keep repeating until 2 to 3 cups milk have been used.
Stir into the remaining hot milk and heat slowly using a wooden spoon to constantly stir.
Heat just until mixture coats spoon.
Don't let it boil for it will curdle!
If curdling does occur, beat with an eggbeater.
Cool.
Add vanilla to taste.
Serve in punch cups with a bit of nutmeg and a dollop of whipped cream on top.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meats together.
Drain grease very well.
Cut up cheese; add to meat and melt on medium-low heat.
Add spices; mix well. Spread mixture on bread.
Bake for 10 minutes on 400°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed on packages for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, poke holes with wooden spoon handle throughout the cake.
Mix together pina colada mix and the condensed milk and pour over entire cake.
Let cool completely. Spread Cool Whip over top of cooled cake and sprinkle with coconut and almonds.
Enjoy!

title: orange balls
directions: Roll wafers into fine crumbs.
Blend in butter.
Work in thawed juice, sugar and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form into small balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: v-8 tomato juice cocktail
directions: Wash and quarter tomatoes with peeling.
Boil until ready to run through colander.
Add remaining ingredients to juice; bring to a boil and can.
I usually pressure this at 5 pounds for 5 minutes after I put it in quart jars.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine graham crackers and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with graham cracker mixture.
Stir in vanilla, pecans, pineapple and coconut; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: lucious layered dessert
directions: Combine flour, oleo and pecans.
Press mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add half carton of thawed Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Whip pudding mix with milk until thickened and pour over the cream cheese layer.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip over the top.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cinnamon carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Add oil and stir. Add eggs all at once.
Stir well.
Add carrots. Mix well.
Bake in two layer pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: zucchini tarte
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May be eaten warm or cold!

title: bentley's dutch potatoes
directions: Core potatoes.
Draw a hot dog through each potato.
Place in baking pan with oil or bacon drippings.
Add milk and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix with rest of ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Chill for 45 minutes or until you can form a ball.
Roll in reserved pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish (9 x 13-inch or 2-quart round). Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over margarine. Top with peaches mixed with cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Line Twinkies in bottom of glass pan.
Pour pudding over Twinkies, then spread pineapple over the top.
Spread Cool Whip. Sprinkle pecans over the top.
Garnish with cherries.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight and serve very cold.
Easy and delicious.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Bring to a boil the Jell-O, pineapple and sugar; let cool. Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip; pour pineapple mixture into Cool Whip mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add beaten eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper to the grated corn.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the cream.
Melt the fat in a frying pan.
Drop corn mixture by spoonfuls into the hot fat. Brown on both sides.
Makes 16 to 18 fritters.

title: camping veggies in skillet
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion; add sliced zucchini and saute until partially done.
Add corn and stir.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Place all ingredients except Certo in pan and bring to a boil over high heat and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and Certo. Put in jelly glasses or jars and seal.

title: hot diggety dogs
directions: Boil frankfurters until just done and place in buns on cookie sheet.
Mix all other ingredients to make a relish.
Place a generous amount of relish on each hot dog.
Bake about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Allow at least two per person, four for teenage boys.

title: oven fried pies
directions: I use 1 quart fresh frozen apples already cooked and sweetened. Cook in microwave until thick enough to spread.
Cool completely. Add spices.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick.
Salt each slice and place on top of each other on plate.
Weight with a heavy plate. Drain when ready to use and dry each piece.
Beat the egg.
Add milk.
Dip each slice in egg and then in crumbs.
Fry brown in deep fat.
Serve while crisp and hot.
With a salad, this makes a cheap meatless meal.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Punch holes all over cake.
Mix jello as directed on box.
Let cool until it begins to thicken.
Pour over cake evenly.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk; mix in Cool Whip and spread this mixture over cake.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Arrange all the thin sliced potatoes on a stone; brush on melted butter. Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with sour cream or chives.

title: hi-rollers
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Grind olives, onion, shaved ham and cheese (as much of each as you'd like).
Blend both mixtures together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tortillas and cut into 1-inch slices.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: moravian mints
directions: Boil sugar and water together until a small amount of it dropped in cold water forms a small ball (234° on candy thermometer).
Add flavoring.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture thickens.
Drop from spoon, forming thin patties onto waxed paper.
Keep candy over hot water while forming patties. Cool.
Makes 4 dozen small mints.

title: orange-pineapple dump salad
directions: Dump all in large bowl.
Mix well and refrigerate. Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: carter's lasagna deliciousa
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain. Cook sausage, ground beef, onion and garlic in large skillet over medium-high heat until sausage is no longer pink and onion is tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, 2 teaspoons of the salt, basil, fennel seeds and pepper. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.

title: hot reuben dip
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve on party rye bread or crackers.

title: grape jello delight
directions: Get water almost boiling (do not let boil).
Add grape Jell-O, crushed pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well.
Put in pan; chill for 3 hours, or until it becomes jello-like.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until bubbles appear around edges of pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla and cream.
Pour in freezer can and place dasher in place.
Freeze following directions with freezer.

title: cherry dumplings
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a medium size frying pan with a tight fitting lid.
Gradually add juice drained from can of cherries; add a few drops red food coloring.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add cherries; heat to bubbling hot. Remove 4 biscuits from can and place on top of cherries; simmer, tightly covered for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: anytime broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients. Mix in the egg, then add milk and vanilla. Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg. Add to creamed mixture. Fold in oatmeal and either raisins or chocolate chips. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes. Makes 24 cookies.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Best if marinated overnight.
Use cooking spray like Pam on cooking sheet.
Place marinated wings side by side.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn pieces over and bake again for 30 minutes.

title: banana shake
directions: Put all ingredients in	blender
on medium speed for 30 seconds.

title: aloha sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in their jackets until just tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Let cool, then peel and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
In a large skillet, melt preserves and butter.
Add sweet potatoes to skillet.
Cook gently, tossing lightly until potatoes are glazed.
Excellent with Kahlua Pork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Don't drain corns.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Mix ingredients together except soup.
Pat on a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in 16 pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Place in baking pan.
Add 1 can mushroom soup (pour and spread over the hamburger).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken squares(for leftover chicken or turkey)
directions: Blend cream cheese, chicken, salt, milk, onion and pimento together.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles or triangles. Spoon 1/4 or 1/4 cup of mixture on dough depending on size you make. Fold and seal all sides.
Brush with melted butter. Roll in flavored bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Pack in a glass 13 x 9-inch dish and put in icebox.
Cut in squares when chilled.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Unfold phyllo and cut sheets in half crosswise.
Phyllo dries out quickly so keep it covered with a barely damp dish towel, when not working with it.
Place 1 sheet on piece of wax paper and brush lightly with butter.
Place cheese in middle.
Starting with 1 corner, bring up pastry to enclose cheese.
Pat gently, then brush with butter to smooth wrinkles and folds.
Turn cheese smooth side up.
Continue wrapping with remaining sheets and butter brush phyllo turning cheese over each time.
Brush top and sides with remaining butter.
Place cheese smooth side up on plate.
Freeze hard.
Wrap airtight.
Label.
Return to freezer.
To bake (450°), place Brie smooth side up on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until phyllo is lightly browned and cheese thawed.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cool cucumber soup
directions: Chop cucumber and cut onions into one-inch lengths.
Place in blender or food processor.
Add 2 cups of the buttermilk, mustard, dill, salt and pepper; blend on high speed for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour into large container and add remaining buttermilk.
Stir well.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: rosemary grilled new potatoes
directions: Mix together in a bowl the garlic and oil.
Toss with new potatoes.
Place potatoes in foil.
Cover potatoes with rosemary sprigs, salt and pepper to taste and butter pieces.
Seal foil bundle and place on top of hot grill or in oven.
Cook approximately 20 minutes or until potatoes pierce easily with a fork.

title: quick cookie
directions: Mix together (can add raisins, coconut, nuts, chocolate chips or whatever you like).
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup to 230°.
Add peanuts and boil to 310°.
Remove from heat and add butter or margarine and baking soda.
Stir and pour immediately onto a buttered cookie sheet.

title: brandied ricotta(fruit dip)
directions: Beat all together.
Mound on serving plate in center.
Cover and refrigerate.
Can be done the day before.
Serve with fruit and Lorna Doones.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In a bowl, sift meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
In a separate bowl, beat 3 eggs lightly and stir in milk and oil.
Add this liquid mixture to dry mixture and then combine all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into two well-greased 9 x 11-inch baking pans.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice(casserole dish)
directions: *Please cut up celery, green pepper and onion.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in casserole dish.
Peel and slice apples and place in buttered dish.
Cut bread into slices and cover apples.
Mix the sugar, egg, 1 stick of melted butter and vanilla; pour over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Freeze biscuits for 1 to 2 hours before using.
When frozen, cut biscuits into quarters.
Place cut biscuits in shaker bag containing 3/4 cup sugar and 1 heaping teaspoonful cinnamon.
Coat with sugar mixture.
Place in a pan. Boil the remaining ingredients for 3 minutes.
Drizzle over bread. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat the ingredients for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° in 2 layer pans or one sheet pan for 25 minutes.
Frost cool cake.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop unpopped corn.
Place in brown grocery bag that has not been recycled (check bottom of bag).
In saucepan bring to boil sugar, margarine
and
Karo;
boil for two minutes.
Pour over popcorn in sack
and
shake.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake;
microwave	again
for 1 1/2 minutes.
Repeat for a total of three times.
Serve.

title: pizza crust
directions: Add warm water to 1-quart bowl. Add yeast and sugar to water. Stir to dissolve. Add oil, then flour and salt and mix thoroughly with wooden spoon or fork. Let rise 5 to 10 minutes. Press into bottom of greased cookie sheet or pizza pan. Add toppings as desired. Bake at 400° until done.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with a fork.
Add next two ingredients and mix with fork.
Combine and bake as directed for pie.
Makes two shells.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in a pie plate or platter the avocados sprinkled with garlic powder, salt and lemon juice.
Spread with sour cream.

Put chili dip on top of sour cream, then layer chopped green onions (stems too) and tomato, then chopped black olives (these could go on top of cheese), then grated Monterey Jack and sharp Cheddar. Keep in refrigerator until serving.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
While broccoli is cooking, melt cheese and 1/4 stick of butter in microwave stirring occasionally until smooth.
Crush crackers and pour remainder of melted butter with crumbs.
Line a dish with the crumb/butter mixture reserving 1/4 for top.
Mix the melted cheese/butter mixture with the drained broccoli and pour into crumb-lined dish. Cover top of casserole with the reserved crumbs and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple noodle pie
directions: Spread the cooked noodles in an oiled 9-inch pie pan.
Spread the apple over the noodles. Drizzle with honey and cream. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cordials
directions: Spoon a small amount of chocolate into each of 24 paper or foil candy cases. Coat sides and bottoms well.
Chill not more than 5 minutes to set chocolate.
Combine Kirsch and grenadine syrup. Chill well.
Place cherry in each case.
Drizzle enough Kirsch mixture over each cherry to cover halfway. Spoon melted chocolate over each cherry to fill case. Chill 5 minutes or until chocolate is set.
Place in airtight container.
Let stand at least 24 hours before using.
Peel casings from candy. Eat carefully, syrup will drip.
Yields 24.

title: frozen yogurt bars
directions: With cheese, onion and boiled egg cut into slices inside of a corn tortilla, fry in hot oil.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, fruit cocktail, nuts and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter-lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, basting frequently.
Yields 4 servings.
This may be served on cooked rice, also.

title: munchy crunchies
directions: Melt morsels over low heat.
Add noodles and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: apple pudding
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda together and stir into creamed mixture.
If lemon juice is used, add 1 Tbsp. more flour to batter.
Turn into a bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° or more for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in greased pan.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: vada's salad dressing
directions: Mix together, sugar, flour, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Then add eggs.
Add cream last.
Cook till thick.
Can be kept for several weeks.

title: taco casserole i
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet brown the beef, then drain off excess fat.
Remove from heat; add garlic powder, taco seasoning mix and the tomato sauce to beef.
Mix and set aside.
In a medium sized bowl combine sour cream and cottage cheese; set aside.
Place half the crushed chips in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish that has been coated with a nonstick spray.
Add enough meat mixture to cover the chips, then cover the meat with half the sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with half the grated cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes, until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.

title: jessica's jamaican pork
directions: Heat Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Stir in curry powder.
Cut bananas into 1/2-inch slices.
Add to skillet.
Saute until golden brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add meat to skillet.
Saute until golden brown.
Stir in pineapple juice and minced onion.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in coconut and bananas. Toss lightly.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 495 calories, fat 12 g (106 cal or 21% of total calories), sat fat 4 g (8% of total calories), carb 59 g, protein 37 g., chol 105 mg, sodium 95 mg.

title: man cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in large Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Cool; cut in squares in pan.
Take out; roll in powdered sugar.

title: linguine with summer sauce
directions: Bring tomatoes and garlic to boil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer until reduced to 1 1/4 cups, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Season tomato sauce to taste with salt.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Drain well.

title: pink party pie
directions: Mix defrosted lemonade with can of milk. Fold in defrosted Cool Whip. Add a few drops of red food coloring and stir. Add to pie shell. You can decorate the top with party sprinkles/nonpareils to make it extra special!
Refrigerate a few hours until solid.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight; drain water.
Add all ingredients to peas. Cook 4 to 5 hours in large pot over low heat, stirring occasionally or cook in slow cooker 8 to 10 hours on low.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hunter's chili
directions: Brown onions, Hamburg, and sausage in dutch oven (skillet) and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together well, except shredded cheese.
Cook on High 10-15 minutes and then simmer 30-45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve topped with small amount of grated cheese.
Yields:
6 - 8 servings.
You may freeze leftover chili.

title: swiss steak and polenta
directions: Brown onion, garlic and celery leaves in drippings until tender.
Brown steak on both sides.
Add seasonings, mushrooms, tomato sauce and water and cook until done, about 1 1/2 hours. Serve with polenta.
Grated cheese is optional.

title: angel salad
directions: Combine all together.
Allow to mellow a few hours in refrigerator before serving on lettuce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend mushroom soup with milk, salt and pepper.
In a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish arrange alternate layers:
potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter and bake for 1 hour at 375° covered.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine
in 9 x 13 inch cake pan, then add sugar and pretzels; mix well.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Beat until fluffy. Spread
on cooled
pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries.
Cool before putting on cream cheese. Spoon on so you don't make holes in cream cheese.

title: what's it cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sour cream and flour like pie crust and separate into 3 balls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Roll out each ball like you would for pie crust.
Mix together nuts, 2 tablespoons granulated sugar and cinnamon and spread over each ball of dough you rolled out.
Then roll each separately so that you have a long roll (1 foot long).

title: low-fat taco salad
directions: Brown turkey and add taco seasoning as directed on package. Simmer 10 minutes.
Put Tostitos in oven at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Place Tostitos on a plate, add meat, desired vegetables, cheese and sour cream.
Delicious.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine according to directions.
Heat butter and cook garlic about 1 minute.
Stir in flour and juice from clams.
Bring to a full boil, stirring.
Add clams, parsley, thyme and basil. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with hot linguine.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Cut peeled potatoes, slanted diagonally, about 1/4 inch thick; put in bowl.
Slice onion over potatoes.
Cut celery and carrots and put over onion and potatoes.
Pre-boil sausage; cut slanted diagonally.
Season to taste.
Cover.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 3 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pheasant in orange sauce
directions: Wash pheasant and pat dry with paper towel.
Sprinkle on both sides with paprika.
Heat 2 tablespoons of margarine in a skillet and cook pheasant until well browned on both sides.
Add margarine if needed.
Mix water and bouillon and pour over pheasant.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Add water if needed and turn meat several times.

title: lemon or raisin sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Cook until thickened. Add juice, butter and lemon peel.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Remove skin from chicken and debone.
Make cornbread dressing as usual.
Place chicken in bottom of pan.
Cover with cornbread dressing, then mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until you form a big ball, then make little balls about 3/4-inch in size.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon bread
directions: First combine dry ingredients.
Beat well the eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add rind of large lemon.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Bake.
While bread is still warm, but not hot, pour the juice of 1 large lemon mixed with 1/2 cup sugar over bread.
Loosen sides so juice goes in and down.
Makes a nice glaze.
Cool before removing.
Bake day before using.
Can be frozen.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix well and chill several hours or overnight.

title: hawaiian pilaf
directions: Fry sausage and drain. Add pepper, onion, celery and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in shallow pan at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered. Freezes well before baking.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cube.
Combine soup and Ro-Tel.
Heat and stir occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: margie's chili
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil until onion becomes somewhat transparent.
Add Vegeburger and continue sauteing until Vegeburger is browned.
Transfer mixture to large kettle.
Add drained kidney beans and pinto beans with liquid.
Peel and blanch tomatoes; chop and add to kettle.
Next, include tomato sauce and water and cook on medium heat until tomatoes are semi-cooked. Season as desired with suggested seasonings.

title: chokecherry jelly
directions: Put all ingredients into pot and cook following pectin instructions or if you don't want to use pectin, cook juice, sugar and syrup to jelly point.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Wipe off jars before putting on lids that are hot.
Twist on tight and they will seal.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat butter.
Add onion, carrot, green pepper and celery.
Saute 6 to 8 minutes or until soft, but not browned.
Turn vegetables in a blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade.
While processing, add flour and broth. Return to saucepan and bring to a boil, whisking constantly until soup thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for about 10 minutes.
Whisk in cheese a handful at a time.
Cook until cheese dissolves, then pour in 1 cup of milk, adding 1/2 cup more if soup is too thick.
Taste for seasoning and add salt and white or red pepper.
Heat to serving temperature.
Soup is good either hot or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas fried turkey breast
directions: Fill a large, deep pot half full of oil. Heat oil over medium high to 350°. Season turkey with salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning. Dredge turkey in flour, then in milk, and back into flour. CAREFULLY lower the turkey into the hot oil and fry until golden brown and cooked to 165° on meat thermometer.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and skin.
Spread the following over the chicken in long cake pan or casserole dish: 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of celery soup and 1 can Pet milk (small).
Mix and add 1 tablespoon sage, 1 package Pepperidge Farm corn bread mix and 1 can chicken broth.
Add corn bread mix last, so it will be on the top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: crowd pleasing slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onions in large casserole dish ending with cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar and celery seed over cabbage.
Bring to a boil vinegar, salt and mustard.
Add oil and bring to a boil again.
Pour over top of cabbage.
Do not mix.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
(Best if refrigerated overnight.)
Will keep for several weeks.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken and Veg-All in greased casserole dish.
Combine and heat soup and broth. Pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over layers and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place eggplant slices in 1-quart casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and Italian seasoning.
Top with spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes; uncover and continue baking for 20 to 25 minutes until eggplant is tender and cheese bubbly.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Sift together into bowl the flour and salt.
Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal. Combine egg yolk, slightly beaten, and enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Slowly add to flour mixture; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in half.
Roll half into a rectangle, about 17 x 12-inch.
Place in greased jelly roll pan, bringing the pastry up the side.
Sprinkle corn flakes over the pastry.
Arrange sliced apples evenly over corn flakes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Roll out other half of pastry and place over apples.
Moisten edges with milk and pinch top layer to bottom.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff and brush over top crust.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
While still warm, glaze with a confectioners sugar glaze.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Place ingredients in a large microwavable bowl.
Melt at 50% power until melted, for approximately two minutes, stirring at one minute.
Stir well.
Pour half of mixture in greased pans, one 9 x 13-inch and one 8 x 8-inch.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O packages separately using 1 cup boiling water for the lemon Jell-O and 2 cups for each of the 6 ounce boxes of different flavored Jell-O.
Stir marshmallows into lemon Jell-O and set aside.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to one Jell-O mixture for bottom layer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set but not firm.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to the other Jell-O mixture for the top layer.
Set aside at room temperature.
Add cream cheese to lemon mixture.
Beat until blended and chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in mayonnaise, Dream Whip and crushed pineapple.
Chill until very thick.
Spoon gently over bottom Jell-O.
Chill until set but not firm.
Meanwhile, chill top Jell-O until thickened, then pour over lemon Jell-O mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 cups.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: penuche
directions: Butter loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cook sugar, milk, syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally to 234° on candy thermometer or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball and flattens when removed from water.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine.
Cool mixture to 120° without stirring.
(Bottom of saucepan will be lukewarm.)
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously and continuously for 5 to 10 minutes or until candy is thick and no longer glossy (mixture will hold its shape when dropped from spoon).
Quickly stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl. Allow foam to settle. Pour into ice cream freezer. Freeze according to manufacturers instructions.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: Remove bone and fat from steak.
Cut into thin strips.
Dredge in flour.
Brown in large skillet.
In hot oil, add onion, broth, thyme and liquid from mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
