Add mushrooms and peas; cover.
Cook 7 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.
Garnish with pimentos.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package, adding green chiles.
Cool after baking.
Crumble 1/2 cornbread into large bowl. Layer remaining ingredients in following order:
1 can beans, 1 c. salad dressing, 1/2 chopped green pepper, 1 can corn, 1 chopped tomato, 1/2 container bacon bits, 1/2 shredded cheese, 1/2 green onions.
Repeat layers, beginning with crumbled cornbread.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: no-bake fruitcake
directions: Mix graham crackers and Milnot in large bowl until milk is absorbed.
Add rest of ingredients, mix well and press tightly into buttered angel food cake pan.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Loosen around edge of pan and turn onto plate.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: Drain and quarter artichokes.
Drain water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8.

title: south of the border enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute onions approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in diced chicken, chiles and cream cheese; set aside.
In a separate skillet, quickly fry tortillas one at a time.
Turn once when they start to blister. Drain on paper towels.
Spoon chicken mixture on the center of each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in a glass baking dish.
Top with sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes, until cream thickens and the cheese bubbles.
Serve with salsa.

title: mud cookies
directions: Mix and bring to boil for 2 minutes, then remove from burner. Add 1/4 cup peanut butter and 4 cups oats.
Mix well and spoon out into balls on cookie sheet.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemonade. Put in graham cracker crust. Chill 2 hours.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Beat margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and eggs together well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture. Add raisins, dates, nuts, coconut and zucchini to other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry topping
directions: Place strawberries and sugar in large bowl; beat until blended and berries are dissolved.
Beat in egg white for 15 minutes at high speed.
Mixture will thicken.
Serve on slices of cake.

title: fruit cocktail cake and topping
directions: Mix in order given and bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice.
Simmer in tightly covered saucepan with onion and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in flour and cheese.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Mix cream and egg yolks, and pour over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes until golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: pepper bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix the two mixtures together and add the remaining ingredients.
Drop from a spoon or shape into rounds on cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: In a bowl, mix together 1/2 cup flour, egg and salt.
Add enough beer to make a thin batter.
Dredge fish in flour and then into batter.
Fry in hot grease.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour.
Bake at 325° (or less) for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: sea leg spread
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth.
Fold in La Creme.
Put half of mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle with caramel topping and sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.
Repeat layer. Freeze.
Serve directly from freezer.

title: amaretto 2
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
(Do not boil.) Cool.
Then add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into sterilized bottles.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt.
Moisten with mayonnaise.

title: sangria
directions: Combine lime juice, lemon juice, orange juice, sugar and wine. Chill.
Before serving, add club soda and garnish.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: congealed asparagus salad
directions: Use juice of asparagus and of tomatoes for liquid in making Jell-O.
Let Jell-O set until thickened, then add other ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: yummy sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sugar, vanilla and 4 tablespoons butter. Add eggs and mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with a mixture of brown sugar, flour, pecans and 4 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over broccoli, sliced fresh mushrooms and sliced green onions.
Mix well so all vegies are coated.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: low fat banana muffins
directions: Combine the dry ingredients; add milk, applesauce, bananas and egg whites.
Put into muffin pans and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: da-da's party dip
directions: Saute chopped pecans in butter to spread over top.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook corn meal and water until it forms a ball, remove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop by teaspoon in hot oil to cook.
Everyone loves them!

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and shortening; add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix soda, rolled oats, flour and coconut together.

Add to first mixture. Shape into 2 long 3-inch rolls in wax paper. Refrigerate until firm. Slice in 1/4 inch thick slices. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: broiled flounder fillets with mustard
directions: Preheat broiler.
Sprinkle fillet halves with salt and pepper. Brush with oil.
Arrange on pan.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and parsley and brush evenly over the fillets.
Place under broiler about 3 or 4 inches from heat.
Broil about 1 minute or until golden brown on top and the fish is cooked through.
Serve with lemon wedges to 4.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash in enough water to cover until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add sour cream, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers (don't crush). Put them all the way to edges.
Prepare pudding according to the directions on the box.
Fold in Cool Whip with the pudding.
Pour over top of the graham crackers.
Put more graham crackers on top. Put the frosting in a bowl and microwave until thin, about 30 seconds.
Spread over top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Add cloves to hot tea for 10 to 15 minutes; strain.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Simmer with 1 stick cinnamon.

title: onion and cheese bake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter on roast (medium high) for one minute, and seasonings.
Roll chicken to coat and cover with wax paper.
Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn pieces over and top with mushrooms. Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle on onion rings and grated cheese.
Cook uncovered on High for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: granola bars
directions: Spread in cookie sheet, well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and peas in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Top evenly with cheese, then bacon and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover pan tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out bread dough to 1/2 or 1-inch thick.
Cover with butter, then cover with a thin layer of cinnamon and a thin layer of brown sugar.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut in about 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in a baking pan and let rise until well doubled in size.
Bake at 350° just until they begin to turn brown.
Remove from pan; let cool until just barely warm.
Cover with icing.

title: honeydew melon stew
directions: Cook brown rice over fire until steaming.
Do not rinse.
Take rice off fire and let stand.
Chop honeydew melon and cantaloupe into medium to small squares.
Place in large 12-inch skillet. Turn fire on low and add tomato sauce.
Slice onions into mix.
Let this mixture simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
Season to taste. When mixture is done, serve over brown rice.

title: pork chops cacciatore
directions: Brown chops in oil over medium heat for 20 minutes, turning once; remove chops.
Cook onion and garlic in pan drippings, 2 to 3 minutes; drain fat if necessary.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms and liquid, Parmesan cheese and basil; stir well.
Return chops to pan.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 to 25 minutes or until pork chops are tender, stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Drain noodles.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add soups.
Toss into noodles.
Stir in chicken.
Cover with grated Velveeta cheese and bake until brown and bubbly at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans, discarding imperfect ones.
Cover with cold water. Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain; add more water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3/4 hour.
Drain.

title: pumpkin chocodot bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add pumpkin, sugar, oil and cereal.
Mix well and add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean, in ungreased Bundt pan at 350°.
You may use regular or mini loaf pans.
Adjust baking time accordingly.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and heat and serve.
People always want this recipe when we serve it.

title: grandma's cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Pour Eagle Brand over this and bake for 20 minutes (or until lightly browned).
In saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer. Cool a while, then chill before cutting.

title: chili
directions: Put oil in large soup pot over medium-low heat.
Add chopped onion and garlic and cook until translucent.
Add ground chuck and sausage; brown very well and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not drain off kidney beans or stewed tomatoes and chop mushrooms before adding.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Using boiling water, mix Jell-O and marshmallows, stirring until marshmallows are dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until slightly thick; then add crushed pineapple, nuts and cream cheese. Cream cheese should be at room temperature.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix together and chill. This makes a rather small bowl; you may wish to double recipe.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix. Put batter in greased muffin tin and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 muffin size biscuits.

title: fried corn with bacon
directions: Fry bacon and put on paper towel to drain.
Crumble and set aside.

title: scallops casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 450° until done.
Cool before putting on icing.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Arrange salted and peppered pieces of chicken in a loaf pan in a single layer.
Add rice.
Add soups mixed with water.
Grate onion over chicken.
Bake for 2 hours at 375°.

title: old timey vegetable soup
directions: Dice potatoes and onion and cook together for 10 minutes. Add other ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce heat and let simmer for 30 minutes. (Other vegetables can be added, as much as you like.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour pan (I use a Bundt pan).
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and mix together.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Add pineapple rings on top of this mixture. Top with cherries and pecans. Prepare cake as directed except use 1/2 pineapple juice instead of full amount of water.
Chopped nuts may be added to mix.
Cook as directed on box and enjoy.

title: fudge icing
directions: In saucepan mix all ingredients and dissolve over low heat. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: keeflies
directions: Mix flour and butter like pastry; add beaten yolks and cream; work until dough is smooth.
Roll into long rolls as for icebox box cookies.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 24 hours (couple of days is better).
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut these into four pieces and roll in palm of hands into balls.
Put on slightly floured board and roll each paper thin.
Fill with following nut filling.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Cook in Bundt pan.

title: magic letter balls
directions: *Or omit peanuts or raisins and use 5 cups Post-Alpha-Bits cereal.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange in shallow 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.

title: orange supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs together; blend until smooth.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Flour nut meats lightly and fold into the batter with the vanilla.

title: golden carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs and beat.
Add carrots and flour, coconut and mix.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add milk, flour, soda and salt.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Remove from oven while hot.
Set on a platter.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix these together and let stand.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Using scissors, snip bacon strips into small pieces into 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes; stir after 2 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove cooked bacon pieces to paper towels to drain.
To bacon drippings in casserole add sugar and cornstarch; blend well.
Stir in salt, pepper and vinegar. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, until thick.
Add drained beans and onion slices to sauce in casserole; stir well.
Cover; microwave on High 6 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Let compote stand 10 minutes before serving to blend flavors.
Sprinkle cooked bacon pieces over top and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 first course servings or 4 to 5 servings as vegetable.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In a large bowl mix margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and egg.
Put into another bowl the flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add flour mixture to first bowl and mix well.
Dough should be soft and easy to handle.
Add a tablespoon of flour if dough is too sticky.

title: easy no cook divinity
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
On low speed or by hand, blend in powdered sugar.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When top side of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry 12 hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: fire and ice tomatoes or 3 bean salad
directions: Boil the last 4 ingredients one minute.
While hot, pout over all vegetables except cucumbers.
Let cool, then add cucumbers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cube bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.

title: gingersnaps(toledo blade)
directions: Mix well together, molasses, sugar and butter.
Then add the ginger and soda.
Stir thoroughly.
Add flour enough to roll well. Roll thin.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine sugar and pudding mix together. Add crushed pineapple with juice. Stir in sour cream.
Stir well.
Pour immediately into prepared crust and place in refrigerator.

title: bun pudding
directions: Place buns split with brown sides up.
Melt butter.
Pour over buns.
Beat eggs, sugar, milk and flavoring.
Pour over buns.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed cottage cheese
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste and refrigerate before serving.

title: rice-cooker sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Place all ingredients together in electric rice cooker.
Stir just enough to blend.
Put cover on rice cooker; press button just as you would to cook rice.
When the bell rings on cooker the jambalaya is ready.

title: cocoa pie(over 50 years old)
directions: Beat eggs and add water.
Sift sugar, flour and cocoa and place in heavy saucepan.
Stir 1/3 cup of egg mixture into dry ingredients to form smooth paste.
Then stir in the rest of egg mixture.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and add to top of pie.
Brown meringue in oven or under broiler.

title: everything september
directions: In a large pot, combine the carrots and all the potatoes.
Add the orange juice, water, salt, pepper and onion powder.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add the butter and honey.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 hours, or until the vegetables are tender.
Continue simmering and sprinkle in the flour, stirring, until slightly thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, soda and salt together, then mix cooking oil, milk, eggs and creamed corn together, then combine the two.
Layer the combined things and then the cheese, beef, onion and chilies in a greased pan.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free fried apples
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add apples.
Saute until light brown.
Add apple juice. Reduce.
Remove from heat.
Add Equal and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Goes well with waffles and pork dishes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted butter and spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, then add pintos and tomatoes and salt to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix corn meal with buttermilk and oil.
Pour corn meal mixture over pinto mixture. Bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in mixer bowl and whip. Add lemon juice.
Fold in drained fruit and nuts.
Pour in crust and let set.

title: tabouli
directions: Pour boiling water over bulgur.
Let stand 2 hours.
Put in colander.
Top with plate to drain.
Put lemon juice and olive oil in blender.
Blend in parsley and mint.
Chop tomatoes and onion. Mix all ingredients and chill.
Keeps well overnight.

title: easy way roast beef
directions: Have roast at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper roast and place on rack in shallow pan.
Place in oven and leave for 1 HOUR.
TURN OVEN OFF, BUT DO NOT OPEN DOOR!
Leave roast in oven for 3-4 hours.
About 30 minutes before dinner, turn oven to 300° to warm.

title: republican dessert
directions: Combine and mix as for pastry, the butter, flour, sugar and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let it cool.

title: smokey hollow banana caramel pie
directions: Boil unopened can of milk 2 hours (keep covered with water and keep at a full boil).
Let cool before opening.
Slice the bananas in the crust.
Pour milk into crust (will be very thick).
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble the Heath bar and sprinkle on top of the Cool Whip.
Forget the calories and enjoy!

title: devil's delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix all together and bake 45 minutes. Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Stir to blend. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Best if let sit in refrigerator overnight before cooking.
Place in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
To bake, spray muffin tin with Pam cooking spray.
Fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and split layers in half to make four.
Place first layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Cover with layer of strawberries, layer of pineapple with juice and layer of bananas.
Sprinkle with pudding (dry) to help soak up extra juice.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Repeat layers until last layer of cake is on top.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in saucepan over medium heat until transparent.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over prepared rice or noodles.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Heat griddle or pan, lightly grease.
Pour about 3 tablespoons batter per pancake.
Cook on both sides until golden brown.
Makes about nine 4-inch pancakes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix thoroughly the wet ingredients; then stir in the dry items.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell, the edge of which has been fluted high.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; then reduce the heat to 350° and continue to bake for 45 minutes or until pie passes the clean knife test.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine egg and milk in shallow dish; set aside.
Stir together the cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper in another shallow dish.
Dip tomatoes in egg-milk mixture, then cornmeal-flour mixture.
In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons cooking oil over medium heat.
Arrange a single layer of tomato slices in skillet and cook about 2 minutes per side or until golden brown.
Repeat with remaining tomatoes, adding additional cooking oil to skillet as needed.

title: chicken today
directions: Combine soup and milk and set aside.
In large skillet brown chicken in oil.
Add onion and pepper and cook until browned, approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
Add soup mixture and continue cooking on low heat until chicken is tender, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Good served
over rice, potatoes or noodles.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio turkey salad
directions: In a bowl, combine turkey, grapes, onion and 1/2 cup pistachios.
Coarsely chop remaining pistachios; set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, dill or tarragon.
Fold into turkey mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on salad greens. Garnish with a sprinkling of chopped pistachios.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and blend.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, crabmeat, salt, pepper and cheese.
Put in shells or in a casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: bavarian mints
directions: Mix dry fondant, corn syrup, evaporated milk and peppermint oil with mixer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Gradually add melted chocolate, beating at medium speed.
When all is added, whip at high speed for 1/2 minute, then spread out to set on slab or cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook diced potatoes and onions together until tender.
Combine 1 quart milk and margarine.
Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Stir in salmon.
Combine 1/2 cup milk and flour, blending until smooth.
Add to salmon mixture and stir well. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; add salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth according to package directions. In another saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add evaporated milk.
Cook and stir until thickens.
Stir in rice, chicken, broccoli and mushrooms.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: frozen salad
directions: Add 1/8 to 1/4 cup sugar if using fresh strawberries.
Mix cream cheese and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add fruit, mix well, add Cool Whip and put in 9x9 inch dish and freeze.
Set out of freezer a few minutes before serving.
Serve in squares.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Put the dressing or Stove Top stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put the chicken on top of the dressing.
Mix 1/2 cup cold chicken broth with the flour.
Heat the 3 1/2 cups chicken broth and butter or margarine and the eggs.
Mix all together to make gravy. Pour gravy over chicken and dressing.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes, then serve with heated can of chicken gravy.

title: grilled peach halves
directions: Preheat griddle.
Drain peaches; place on paper towels to absorb excess juices.
Brush peaches with butter.
Grill hollow side down 1 1/2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn and grill 1 1/2 minutes longer.
If desired, fill centers with jelly or cranberry sauce.

title: whipped shortbread
directions: Blend ingredients together until fluffy.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Place dough on lightly floured board, roll to desired thickness (1/4 to 1/2-inch) and cut with lightly floured cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge cake brownies
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.
I use the following frosting; it's not too sweet.

title: basic pancakes
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) and stir.

title: yankee noodle bake
directions: Brown franks and cook onions in butter until tender.
Combine cooked noodles, soup, water and mustard in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave rocky road fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted; mix well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator. Cut into squares.
Yield:
36 squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Add margarine and baking soda. Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix in other ingredients and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let the sausage and cheese get to room temperature because it is easier to mix. Just dump everything into a big bowl and combine well. Roll into good size balls, enough for about 2 bites a piece. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbling hot and they begin to brown. These freeze well and heat up in the microwave.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate. Add sugar, coffee and egg yolks. Mix until thickened and remove from heat. Let cool. Add whipping cream. Spoon mousse into individual serving cups and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onions and cook in butter.
Add rice and mix well.
Add chicken stock and bring to boil.
Add bay leaf and white pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes until rice is cooked.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Add small amount of oil to skillet and brown chicken.
Add onions and peppers on top of chicken.
Place several pats of margarine on top of peppers and add Worcestershire sauce.

title: bread and butter pickles(makes 7 pints)
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly; drain.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch slices; discard ends.
Cover with crushed ice; let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar; heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers and heat 5 minutes.
Pack hot pickles loosely into clean, hot pint jars and cover with hot liquid to 1/2-inch from top.
Adjust jar lids.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes (start counting as soon as water returns to boiling).
Add 1 minutes for each 1000 feet above sea level.
Remove jars and tighten seals if needed. Set jars upright; cool.
Set them several inches apart.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Marinate pork chops for at least 6 hours.
Grill chops about 7 minutes on each side.

title: chicken noodle soup with dumplings
directions: Follow directions on soup can.
Bring to a boil.
Cut biscuits in 1/4 or 1/2, whatever you wish.
Drop in boiling soup.
Cover and boil 20 to 30 minutes.
Don't take cover off until after 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onion in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup, carrots and sour cream.
Combine butter and stuffing mix.
Cover the bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with half the stuffing mix; add zucchini mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mix and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: jam sammich
directions: On one slice of bread, spread the peanut butter.
On one slice of bread, spread jam.
Holding one slice on the palm of each hand, jam them together to mix the peanut butter and jam.
Eat while drinking milk.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together. Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Can do ahead.

title: dream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Beat egg yolks and salt until very thick and lemon colored.
Add water.
Beat in and add sugar, gradually beating until thick enough to hold a stiff peak.
Fold egg whites and flour into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake in oven at 350° about 40 minutes.
Invert pan and let cake hang in pan until cool.
Makes 1 (9-inch) cake.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwavable bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.

title: easy punch
directions: Prepare according to package instructions.
Mix to taste. Freeze punch and serve slushy.
Kids love it.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Add all remaining ingredients except egg whites.
Fold beaten egg whites in last. Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: parmesan cheese baked chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk in bowl. In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese. Roll chicken first in egg mix, then in the potato flake mixture. Melt butter in shallow baking pan. Roll coated chicken pieces in the butter; place skin side up in the pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into paper baking cups placed in muffin tins. Freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in a little water until thawed, then drain.
In another pan, melt 1/2 stick butter, cheese and 3/4 cup milk.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli to cheese mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Crumble crackers in butter.
Put cracker mixture on top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool for about 15 minutes before eating.

title: microwave chocolate clusters
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir after 1 minute. Stir in cereal. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 24.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix honey, sugar and eggs.
Mix until light and fluffy, then add shortening, peanut butter, vanilla, flour and soda.
Bake at 325° to 350°.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Good, chewy cookie.

title: orange whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dry orange jello over mixture and stir. Pour mixture into a large salad bowl or trifle bowl; chill.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados in large bowl; cut up onions, lettuce, tomatoes and yellow chiles into small pieces.
Mix with salt, garlic, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until it comes off bone.
Add enough water to broth to make
approximately
cups.
Saute
celery, bell pepper and onion in
margarine before adding to other ingredients.
Cook spaghetti and
broth
minutes.	Add
rest
of ingredients except cheese
and	simmer	about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and stir thoroughly.

title: banana dog
directions: Spread inside of hot dog bug with peanut butter.
Insert peeled banana.
Top with globs of applesauce.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dreamsicle cake i
directions: Mix cake according to box directions and add 1 small box of pudding mix. Bake according to directions. When cake is done, poke holes in cake. In a bowl, mix Jell-O and 1 cup of boiling water; mix until dissolved. Add 1 more cup of hot water and ladle over cake. Put cake in the refrigerator overnight. Then take cake out and set pan bottoms in hot water for a moment; turn upside down on cake plate.

title: mango salsa
directions: Toss all ingredients together gently in a bowl.
Serve within one day.

title: blueberry grunt
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and dash of salt.
Stir in the milk and vanilla.
Pour over melted butter.
Sprinkle blueberries over the top. Bake in a 375° oven about 30 minutes or until golden. Serve with whipping cream or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Slice each layer horizontally into halves. Mix pudding, milk and 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Set aside 1/3 cup.
Cut shortening into rest of flour/salt.
Make paste of water and 1/3 cup flour/salt. Add to flour and shortening mix.
Divide pastry and roll out.

title: hearty rice casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a greased 4-quart baking dish.
Mix well. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Stir together corn and next 6 ingredients in a bowl - cover and chill 2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Grate cheese. Place 1/2 asparagus in greased casserole; add about 1/2 cracker crumbs; then 1/2 of the margarine followed by 1/2 the cheese. Repeat layers. Top with mushroom soup.

title: luncheon tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes into medium thickness.
Spread one slice with flavored cream cheese.
Top with second tomato slice. Dip in beaten egg, then in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Have oil hot, but not too hot, about medium heat.
Fry on both sides. A different taste than fried green tomatoes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water.
Pour over flour, sugar mix and add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and water chestnuts.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Combine margarine with corn flake crumbs; sprinkle on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bacon-cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper on top.
Frost with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Prepare day ahead of time in large bowl.
Tightly cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Using about 1/3 of cake, tear into pieces in punch bowl.
Top with 1 can of pie cherries, then 1/3 whipped topping.
Repeat with 1/3 of cake and 1 can of drained pineapple and 1/3 of whipped topping.
Repeat again with 1/3 of cake and 1 can of cherry pie filling. Finish off with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for several hours.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes. Boil in water until tender; drain water. Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper. Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in 2 cups of cheese, bacon and onions. Put into a greased 3-quart baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend butter and flour.
Add egg yolks and sugar, beaten together.
Add buttermilk and lemon extract.
Pour in two pastry-lined pie tins.

title: dad's barbecue marinade(good on chicken, pork, steak and beef.)
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate with either chicken, pork, steak or beef overnight.

title: cheesy ham and noodle bake
directions: Saute pepper and onion.
In a bowl, gradually add milk to soup; add sauteed bell pepper and onion.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with vegetable oil spray and layer one-half each of noodles, ham, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Add milk to soup and mix well.
Combine soup mix, beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish with lid.
Add onions or crumbs on top.
If using potato chips, crush into small crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mash, knead and squeeze. Form into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Place each on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass.
Dip it in sugar and mash the balls flat.
Butter glass once or twice but dip in sugar for each ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes about 14 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In large skillet, brown onion and ground beef.
Drain off fat. Add rice and mix in skillet.
Fill peppers with mixture.
In baking dish (casserole style), pour sauce and water in dish, then stand peppers up in dish.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain lima and butter beans.
Mix all beans together.
Cut bacon into small (1-inch) pieces.
Fry bacon and diced onions. Mix beans, bacon, onion and remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hershey cocoa syrup
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add enough water to make a paste, then add remainder.
(Gets lumps out.)
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Add in order given.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: calico beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Fry bacon, onions and hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: flying saucers
directions: Prepare whipped topping with 1/2 cup milk as directed on package.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 12 cookies.
Top with remaining cookies, pressing lightly.
Freeze 3 hours before serving.

title: granny's dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
On floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into squares.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter. Add seasoning, cornbread and bread crumbs. Mix well, then add eggs. Add soup and place in casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and stir into butter mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and add dry ingredients with milk.
Fold berries in last.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and add the Topping.

title: appetizer meat balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Let stand 10 minutes. Shape into small balls.
Heat next 4 ingredients together over low heat until jelly is melted, blending well.
Place meat balls in sauce.
Cook over low heat.
Turn each meat ball over.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; simmer for 10 minutes or until meat balls are done and sauce is thick.
May be made in advance and reheated slowly before serving.
Will keep for 2 to 3 days in refrigerator or frozen will keep 1 month.
Can freeze meat balls and make sauce and cook and serve as needed.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Spread 1/3 pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer; repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted, sliced almonds and pineapple slices, if desired.

title: hobo supper
directions: For each person to be served, place each hamburger patty on a piece of foil about 12 inches squares.
Slice potato and onion on top of patty.
Season potato with a little salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Fold foil over top and ends so juice will remain in package.
Place package(s) on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes to one hour.

title: berry good french toast
directions: Diagonally cut bread in 1-inch slices.
Place in baking dish (set aside).
In medium bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla; stir in milk.
Pour over bread.
Turn slices and cover well.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate cupcakes(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate together. Place sugar, flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup milk, egg, chocolate mixture and remaining milk, mixing well after each addition.
Dissolve baking soda in water and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Fill paper baking cups with batter and place in muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: nine layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed. sprinkle sugar over salad dressing.
Let stand overnight.
Do not toss.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix 1 cup butter, cream cheese and flour to make dough.
Press into miniature cupcake tins to form crusts.
Mix 2 tablespoons melted butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Fill crusts 1/2 full.
Place 1 or 2 whole pecans on each pie, or use crushed pecans to cover each pie.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen tassies.

title: chicken ole(serves 10)
directions: Boil breasts in seasoned water until tender.
Cool; debone. Tear into bite size pieces.
Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except asparagus and almonds.
Simmer sauce until cheese melts.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Tear cake into bite sized pieces.
Soften cream cheese and combine with Dream Whip, whipped with milk.
Toss with cake and press into Pyrex dish.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.
You may use strawberries, blackberries or any fruit you wish.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Layer peeled and sliced fruit on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except fruit, then spread mix evenly over fruit.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion peach cobbler
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup apple juice; stir well and set aside.
Combine peaches, 1 cup apple juice, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Stir in reserved cornstarch mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in almond extract.
Let cool.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour all ingredients, except ice cubes, in blender.
Mix well. Add ice cubes gradually, mixing well.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Spread about 1 teaspoon butter on 1 side of each slice of French bread.
Set aside.
Cook the sliced onions in 2 tablespoons butter about 10 minutes or until onions are tender but not brown, stirring often.
Transfer the onions to a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the Swiss cheese over the onions.
Mix the chicken soup, evaporated milk, and pepper until well blended.
Pour the soup mixture evenly over the cheese layer.
Layer the bread slices, buttered side up, over the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated and bread slices are golden brown.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well; store in airtight container.

title: pistachio squares
directions: Mix and spread first 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Heat cranberry sauce until melted.
Add all other ingredients. Pour over meatballs and heat in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, cooking meatballs to desired doneness.

title: pam's best beer bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients and mix well with a hand beater.
Pour into two loaf pans sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Brush liquid Butter Buds on top after removing from oven.
Serve warm.
Yields 2 loaves (24 slices).

title: chocolate filling for 4 layer cake
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Keep stirring until syrup forms "soft ball."
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread on top of cake layers.

title: microwave-bread pudding
directions: In a deep 1-quart microwavable casserole bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes.
Remove and stir well.
Return to microwave and cook for 4 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate-dipped delights
directions: Insert long wooden picks into fruit to be dipped.
Dip fruits, nuts or pretzels into chocolate, covering at least half; let excess chocolate drip off.
Let stand or refrigerate on wax paper lined tray until chocolate is firm, about 30 minutes.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 days.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash the kidney beans to rid them of excess red and mix all ingredients together; let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Slice top off baked potatoes; scoop insides into mixing bowl. Mash potatoes and beat with butter, milk, salt and pecans.
Refill shell.
Bake in 450° oven for about 5 minutes.

title: slaw overnight
directions: Combine cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage mixture, toss gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: my dad's meat rub(for pork or beef)
directions: Brown meat and cool to your liking.
Using Griffin's Strawberry, Apricot or Peach Preserves, rub over meat and bake last 15 minutes.

title: easy baked potatoes
directions: Spread potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: party punch
directions: This recipe can be made up ahead of time and frozen. But, do not add the Sprite and sherbet until mixture is thawed and ready to serve. Makes 3 gallons. Serves 75.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Combine biscuit mix, 1/4 cup sugar and next 4 ingredients in bowl.
Beat vigorously with a spoon for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Roll immediately in melted butter and mixture of 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Serve hot.
Yields 12 medium muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli. Combine soup, cheese, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Add broccoli last.
Mix together.
Put into buttered casserole.
Put cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits until thin (about the size of a saucer).
Cut in half.
Using 1/4 of apple, roll in biscuit half.
Place in baking dish, cut side down, close but not touching.
Mix together in pan the sugar, margarine, water, lemon juice and apple pie spice or pumpkin pie spice mix.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turkey ala king
directions: Note:
Amounts are irrelevant here.
Make as much or as little as necessary.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salsa and tomato sauce; simmer.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer 1/2 of beef mixture, 6 corn tortillas, 1/2 of cottage cheese and egg mixture (mix well together) and 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese.
Make another layer as directed and bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and store in tightly covered container.
To mix, put 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix into cup and add boiling water; stir. Marshmallows or whipped cream are optional.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package for sheet cake (13 x 9-inch). As soon as cake is taken out of oven, punch holes in it with a knife.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk.
Let cake cool; spread Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle coconut on top.
Then refrigerate.

title: wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion, celery, mushrooms and butter until tender.
Combine with rice, water chestnuts, soup, sour cream and turkey.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered and 30 minutes uncovered, in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and almonds over top of casserole.
Brown slightly under broiler.
Serves 6.

title: apple slices
directions: Crust:
Blend first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Beat egg, egg yolk, lemon juice and cold water.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well and divide dough in half.

title: cafe brulot
directions: Remove white membrane from orange peel (to avoid bitter flavor).
Cut peel into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
In a chafing dish, combine cinnamon, cloves, sugar cubes, lemon peel and orange peel.

title: dunkin platter cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, and sugar, stir in eggs and vanilla. Mix in oatmeal and corn flakes.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder, stir in coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet sprayed with pam.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes. Cookie will spread out on cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: wonderful apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Mix together sugar, flour, apple pie spice and butter until crumbly (use pastry blender or 2 knives).
Spread about one third of this mixture over the bottom of the pastry.
Peel apples, core and cut into slices.
Place in crust.
Spoon remaining sugar mixture over the apples.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about one hour).

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix all ingredients, pressing into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: 0 fat weight-loss soup
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1 hour.
Eat all you want as often as you like.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans and butter, stirring until blended.
Press mixture into sides 1-inch up the bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 375°
for 8 minutes; cool.
Place white chocolate in top of double boiler, bring water to boil. Cook until melted.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese
and sour cream in large mixing bowl, beat at medium speed until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Pour filling into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until set.
Turn off oven and crack door. Leave cake in oven 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion in skillet. Put in a large saucepan; add other ingredients. Cook slow for several hours.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over the crust.
Then spread 4 cups fresh peaches over the first mixture.

title: beef roulade
directions: Tenderize meat with a meat mallet.
Sprinkle each side with salt and pepper.
Spread some mustard on one side of meat.
Lay a strip of bacon on the meat.
Cut pickles into julienne strips and place five or 6 strips of pickles on the bacon.
Roll it up and secure with a toothpick at each end.
Brown onion and meat rolls in a large skillet.
When well browned, add enough water to the skillet to cover the meatballs.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on medium heat.
Add water as necessary to keep meat covered.
Serve with knodel or noodles.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a pan, place oleo, water and cocoa.
Heat to rapid boil.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Season to taste.
Reserve broth. Saute onion, celery, carrot and some parsley in butter.
Add soup and broth.
Continue to stir over medium heat until well blended and hot.
Add torn chicken pieces and stir in noodles.
Serve.

title: popcorn scramble
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix popcorn, Cheerios, Rice Chex and peanuts together.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Heat until boiling.
Cook, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Drizzle over popcorn mixture.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: german meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meatballs in crock-pot.
On medium-high heat, cook 4 hours or until meatballs are done.
The longer they cook, the better they taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Mix soup and tomatoes together.
Put a layer of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer meat.
Add soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: aunt ellen's cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses and allow to soften.
Mix cheeses, garlic cloves, mayonnaise, salt and sauce well.
Shape into balls.
This will make 2 large or several small cheese balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: easy meringue(meringue is not hard to make.)
directions: In a bowl, mix ingredients until stiff.
Pile on top of pie and bake in a 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown. Watch so meringue doesn't burn!

title: chili pinwheels
directions: Put approximately 1 tablespoon on each tortilla and spread it over tortilla.
Roll up and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate and slice just before serving.

title: my mother's pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately to sugar mixture, then add vanilla.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Let cool before frosting.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: raisin carrot cake
directions: Sift
together	the
first 4 ingredients and set aside. Cover raisins
with
warm
water and let stand for 5 minutes. Then drain and blot well with paper towel.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Soak rice in boiling water; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Drain rice and add to mixture.
Put in baking dish and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Combine with sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup margarine. Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased casserole dish. Top with combined brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup margarine and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk and egg.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and margarine, then add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add milk and
flour (about 1/4 mixture at the time), blending well.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake in
a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 335°.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients:
lettuce, celery, pepper, onions, peas, mayonnaise, sugar, bacon bits and cheese in this order.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.
You may add a layer of broccoli or cauliflower, if you desire.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
You may also use strawberry pie filling.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the creamed sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir vanilla, almond extract, flour and salt into mixture.

title: chocolate orange mousse
directions: In heavy pan, melt margarine.
Add cocoa and 2/3 cup milk, stirring until smooth and slightly thickened.
Pour into medium bowl.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat in 1 tablespoon juice and 1 teaspoon rind.
Fold in 1/2 of whipped cream.
In medium bowl, combine rest of milk, juice and rind.
Fold in rest of whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly.
In dessert dishes, spoon in chocolate. Make a "well" in each.
Spoon in orange.
Chill.

title: orange brutus(orange julius)
directions: Put 3 cups orange juice in blender.
Add the vanilla pudding, Dream Whip and vanilla; blend.
Pour into pitcher, then add the other 3 cups of orange juice.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch baking pan (jelly roll pan) with the unrolled sheets of crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
In mixing bowl, combine salad dressing, sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over crescent roll crust.
Combine vegetables and cheese; toss to mix. Distribute evenly over cheese mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and push vegetables into cheese.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into bars and serve.
Makes about 3 dozen small bars.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Cover the cucumber slices, onions and pickling salt with ice cubes.
Mix and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine rest of the ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil. Seal in sterilized jars. Makes 6 pints.

title: german cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Place in bowl in layers, alternating with thinly sliced onion rings.
Top with 7/8 cup sugar.

title: uncooked cheese cake
directions: Stir Jell-O, water and lemon juice together and cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix with Jell-O mixture and then fold in Milnot (whipped).
Place in crust made from graham cracker crumbs and butter.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to full boil.
Remove immediately from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cereal.
Press into buttered 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips; spread as icing over first mixture.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: zesty stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pierce with fork.
Place 1 inch apart on paper towel.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes. Cut strip from top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp.
Stir in sour cream and next four ingredients.
Spoon into shells.
Top with bacon bits and microwave on High until thoroughly heated.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon from fat and drain. Leave about 1 tablespoon of drippings in frying pan. Pour rest away. Allow pan to cool. In a bowl, beat egg. Add flour and sugar. Stir until smooth. Add salt, vinegar and water. Pour into pan with drippings. Cook slowly, stirring until thick and bubbly. Crumble bacon over lettuce or dandelion leaves and pour hot dressing over the top.

title: indian pie
directions: Braise ground meat and onion in frying pan.
Drain off liquid. Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Peel and boil potatoes, when done mash potatoes with milk and butter (a few pats). Combine meat, onion, mixed vegetables and tomato soup. Use only 1/2 can of water. Mix well.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder to taste.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spoon meat mixture into dish to 1/2 from top. Spoon mashed potatoes on top of meat mixture.
You may need 2 baking dishes. Cut pats of butter on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° until butter melts and potatoes start to brown.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Add cherry Jell-O.
Let cool (set in ice water).
When cool, add bananas which were sliced down the middle, then cut in small pieces.
Add chopped pecans. Pour into pie shells.
Top with whipping cream.

title: oven barbecued hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a small bowl, combine crushed pineapple with its juice, chili sauce, apricot preserves, brown sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch. Mix well. Arrange chicken breasts in 8 x 8 or 9 x 13 pan (either lined with foil or sprayed with oil). Spoon pineapple mixture over chicken. Bake chicken 45 to 50 minutes, basting occasionally with pan drippings, until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.

title: quick cobbler or pie
directions: Melt butter in oven while it's preheating to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Combine milk and vanilla with dry ingredients and pour into pan with melted butter.
Pour one quart of can peaches or other fruit (with juice) over batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: penda
directions: In large bowl, mix butter and condensed milk.
Put into microwave oven; cook for 5 minutes on High.
Then add dry milk and mix well.
Put back into microwave oven for 4 minutes.
If not as thick as dough, cook for a few more minutes.
Then cool in refrigerator.
Mold in balls.
Press tops into chopped pistachio nuts.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breast in lemon juice.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cover chicken pieces in the flour mixture.
Put chicken pieces in pan and cook until brown, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: boiled eggs
directions: If time allows bring refrigerated eggs to room temperature. Place eggs in cold water with approximately 1/2 teaspoon salt per egg.
Turn heat between low and medium and go do something else for 20 minutes or so.
Air bubbles can be seen coming from the eggs. If heated too rapidly it will break the egg.
When bubbles stop, turn the heat up and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes; turn off heat.
Let stand 10 minutes or so.
Rinse in cold water.

title: baked herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove skin and excess fat; arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking pan the chicken.
Combine and pour over can of mushroom soup and rest of ingredients.
Bake uncovered 1 1/4 hours. Serve with hot cooked rice or bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Makes a good Sunday chicken dinner.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Melt butter or soften and mix with sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle half the flour over chopped fruit and nuts.
Mix the other half with milk, then mix in fruit and nuts.

title: hershey's kiss brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray miniature muffin cups with nonstick spray.
Melt butter over medium low heat.
Add chips, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring briskly until each is incorporated.
Gradually stir in the flour until blended; add nuts.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake, centers should be moist.
Place Hershey's Kiss on each brownie as soon as removed from oven.
Let cool in pans 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: artichokes stuffed with creamed crabmeat
directions: Remove stems and tough outer leaves from artichokes.
Use scissors to trim the sharp tips remaining on the artichoke leaves. Stand artichokes upright in deep saucepan large enough to hold them snugly.
Add 4 tablespoons salt, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and the olive oil to 2 to 3-inches of water.
Cover and boil gently 45 minutes until tender or until the base can be pierced with a fork. Lift out the cooked artichokes.
Hold the bottom and press each artichoke firmly on your work surface to loosen the leaves. Leave them upside-down to drain on paper towels.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers, onions and cabbage.
Squeeze out excess juice.
Mix vinegar, sugar and seasoning together, then add to ground mixture.
Boil hard for 15 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: crunchy fruit cake
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside.
Beat the eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour over the fruit mixture. Pack in lined, well-greased angel food pan.
Place a pan of water under cake the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix together.
Makes 1 gallon.
Will keep in refrigerator two weeks.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour in greased 9 X 13 casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cake surprise
directions: Mix the pudding and put in refrigerator.
While that is chilling, in a 13 x 9-inch dish, tear off the angel food cake into bite size pieces and place on bottom of dish.
Once pudding is ready, pour over cake.
Next pour cherry pie filling over cake. Voila.
You have a delicious and low-fat (if you follow the low-fat recipe on the cake and pudding) dessert.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix seasonings and dressing mix
in the oil. Stir well and pour over crackers, one box at a time.
(Seems to coat better this way.)
Stir often for the first couple of hours.
Store in tight container.
(Using something like a round Tupperware cake container allows you to shake in order to mix.)
Enjoy!

title: peppy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta to desired doneness.
Drain and allow to cool.
In large bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients thoroughly. Toss in the pasta.
If making ahead of time, you may want to moisten it with a little extra mayo just before serving.
You can also blanch the veggies first if you like them tender.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions using 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Drain and set aside.
Combine pasta, beans, tomatoes, cucumber and salad dressing; toss gently.
Chill.
To serve, add radish and toss gently.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk until well blended.
Melt margarine in cooking dish.
Pour margarine in cooking dish.
Pour mixture of
sugar, flour and milk over melted margarine.
"Do not stir." Place fruit on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: beef pot roast
directions: In skillet, put 1/4 cup of shortening; heat.
Brown both sides of roast.
Remove and place in roasting pan.
Place potatoes and carrots around roast; place onions, salt, pepper and Worcestershire over roast, then add mushroom soup on top.
Cook at 450° for one hour or until roast is ready.
Put cornstarch in water around roast to make gravy.

title: coffee tapioca cream
directions: Put milk, coffee, tapioca, sugar and egg in double boiler and cook until it thickens.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and let it cool.
Before serving, add whipped cream, folding it into tapioca mixture.
Mixture can be made the day before, but do not add cream until 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Simmer chicken in a skillet with water until cooked. Then, add the butter and soy sauce. Cook until soy sauce mixture in one. Served well over rice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken with celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
(Reserve broth.)
Take chicken from bones and chop into bite-sized pieces.
In food processor or blender, mix soup, chilies and 1/2 of the sour cream.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray.
Dip each tortilla in chicken broth to soften.

Hold tortilla in your hand and put in about 2 tablespoons of chicken, a sprinkling of cheeses and a dollop of sour cream. Fold one side of the tortilla over the other side and place, seam side down in baking dish.
When all tortillas are in dish, pour sour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Garnish with sliced black olives and green onions.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken, save broth and add to noodles.
Put all ingredients together.
Cook slowly until done.
Cool right away and put in refrigerator or eat right away.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup of berries and stir by hand.
Grease muffin tins well with butter and tops of pans as well.
Pile mixture high in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle sugar over tops.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for at least 30 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over boiling water.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Shape into balls.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: caramel brownies(heavenly)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix with melted butter, vanilla and 1/2 can of evaporated milk.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in half of cake mixture; bake for 8 minutes.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Mix brown sugar and oil, add eggs and vanilla, and stir.
Mix salt and soda to flour and add to first mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If you like them soft, bake about 15 minutes.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, parsley and salt; blend thoroughly.
(Hint: Bread crumbs chopped in food processor works well for fine texture.)
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in margarine; drain.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken or beef teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken pieces for at least 12 hours.
Marinate steak or sirloin tips for 24 to 36 hours.

title: ham and broccoli hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli.
Strain well.
In saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender.
In large bowl stir together soups, milk, cheese, ham, rice and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Add broccoli and onions.
Put in 2 1/2 or 3-quart pan or casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cook noodles in butter, salt and water.
Brown beef and add season to taste.
Place a layer of noodles, meat and cheese in dish until all used up.
Dilute soup with water and pour over layers. Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes.
Put in a large kettle with all ingredients and mix well.
Heat and stir to boiling point, then cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
It will cook down.
Very good when you make it for Sloppy Joes.
Also good in bean soup.
Put in pint jars while hot and seal (open kettle type).

title: white cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
shortening;
add
dry ingredients and 2/3 cup milk.
Mix well
and
add
egg whites and rest of milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour
in two greased and floured cake pans. Bake in 350° oven until tested done or brown on top.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Combine beans and 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Combine remaining sauce and sour cream.
Mix well.
In a 9-inch pie plate, layer bean mixture, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, olives and cheese; cover.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy strudel
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 2 balls; chill, covered, in plastic wrap, 2 to 3 hours.
Make 2 strudels.
Roll out each part as thin as pie crust on floured surface into a rectangle.
Spread half of filling on dough.
Roll up as in a jelly roll.
Do the same with other half.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
When serving, cut and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Day before:
Mix butter, cheese and salt until creamy.
Mix in flour.
Shape into 14 balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: In a large saucepan, coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add asparagus, broth and red pepper flakes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until asparagus is tender.
Place 1/3 of mixture in a blender; add cream cheese, sour cream and dill. Cover and process until smooth; return to pan.
Cook over medium heat until heated through.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: shrimp-corn 'n cheese chowder
directions: Melt butter in large Dutch oven; add onion, garlic and pepper. Saute until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, corn and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.* Add shrimp; cover, reduce heat and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat until it forms a ball, about 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes nice dough.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: meat gravy
directions: Brown the meat in large skillet.
Add salt, pepper, and flour, stir and let brown slightly.
Add water and milk, stir constantly.
Boil about 5 minutes.

title: upside down caramel apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pineapple butternut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Drain pineapple; reserve and pour juice into a small saucepan. Add raisins to juice and heat to boiling. Let sit until raisins have plumped up and cooled.

title: homestyle potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes (allow two per person).
Boil in salted water. Cut up sausage into bite size pieces and chop the onion and bell pepper.
Saute.
Add parsley and pepper after sauteing.
Set aside.
Drain cooked potatoes.
Over low heat add butter, cream, milk and water, if needed.
Add the sausage mixture and cook for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: punch bowl cake(no bake)
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix sour cream, Cool Whip, evaporated milk and powdered sugar.
Break up into pieces the angel food cake. Place them in a punch bowl.
Pour the mixture over the cake and fold in.
In a separate bowl, combine strawberries and glaze.
Pour over the top of cake mixture.
(Don't mix in.)
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: poppy seed dressing(for fruit salads)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add salad oil slowly, beating well.
Dressing will thicken as oil is added.
Stir in poppy seed.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Slice chicken into thin strips.
In large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, lime juice, hot pepper sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt, pepper and onion and pepper slices.
Add chicken; marinate for 30 minutes or overnight in refrigerator.

title: easy vegetable quiche
directions: Partially bake pie crusts at 400° for 6 minutes on preheated cookie sheet.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Prepare filling:
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook green onions and green peppers with garlic until tender.
In medium bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat together milk, soup, eggs and flour until well mixed.
Stir in onion mixture and pimientos.

title: cherry rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until tender.
Add sugar and stir constantly. Add pie filling and cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and put in refrigerator or freezer.

title: kathy's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt sugar and syrup over low heat. Add crunchy peanut butter and stir until a good consistency. Add Special K cereal. Mix and spread in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a double boiler and pour over bars. Chill in refrigerator approximately 45 minutes. Cut into bars and serve.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat shortening in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches) in oven until melted.
Mix potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg.
Roll in potato mixture.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in pan.
Bake until thickest pieces are done, about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: whipped dessert
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: carolyn's percolator punch
directions: Place cranberry juice, pineapple juice, water and brown sugar in percolator.
Place cloves, allspices and cinnamon in basket of percolator and perk.
Yield:
8-9 servings.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Cut the beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and toss gently with Kitchen Bouquet on all sides. Mix in cream of rice.
Cut carrots and add in along with all other ingredients.
Mix gently.

title: campbell's tomato soup
directions: This is an old family recipe handed down to my brother and me by our father. We have passed it along to our sons. I especially recommend it to the men who aspire to be gourmet cooks without too much fuss and effort.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 3 1/2 c. boiling water.
Add sliced bananas, pineapple, marshmallows.
Let set.
Before serving, spread Miracle Whip over top and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine.
Add thyme, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour; swish each piece in margarine.
Arrange with skin side down.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Turn chicken.
Add wine.
Spread mushrooms over top; cover with foil and continue baking about 30 minutes.

title: french dip roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot or roaster.
Pour soups and beer over roast.
Cover and slow-cook 6 to 8 hours.
